description: The 2019 edition of the Air Jordan 19 Retro ‘Flint Grey’ brings back one of the silhouette’s OG colorways from 2004. 15 years later, the shoe is still unique, highlighted by patent leather construction and a Tech-Flex lace cover inspired by a fencer’s mask. The sleek mid-top rests on a matching white phylon midsole, fitted with a Zoom Air unit for lightweight cushioning.

The Air Jordan 19 Retro ‘Countdown Pack’ launched in 2008 as part of a package release that also include the ‘Bred’ Air Jordan 4. This pair features the same color scheme, highlighted by an all-black upper with subtle red accents on the collar lining and rubber outsole. The shoe’s defining features are a patent leather toe and the Tech Flex shroud that conceals the laces and tongue.

One of the silhouette's OG colorways, the Air Jordan 19 OG 'Bred' 2004 features a familiar Chicago Bulls look. The shoe's signature feature is the Techflex lacing shroud modeled after a venemous African snake. A hook-and-loop strap supports the fit, while patent leather emerges on the toe box. The tonal tooling includes full-length Zoom Air and double-stacked Zoom Air in the heel, with a modified herringbone pattern for traction. The Varsity Red hits are limited to the outsole and lining.

The Air Jordan 19 SE ‘Olympic’ was a special release for the 2004 Athens Games, with a subdued USA color scheme highlighted by metallic gold, most notably on the Jumpman. The white leather upper sports quilted detailing, while Midnight Navy and hits of red complete the patriotic look. The silhouette's signature lace shroud is noticeably absent.

The Air Jordan 19 'Flint' launched in 2004 as the inaugural colorway of the unique silhouette – the first to launch following Michael Jordan’s final retirement from basketball. Designed by Tate Kuerbis, the sneaker draws inspiration from the black mamba snake, featuring a Techflex shroud and white patent leather toe. Performance benefits include a carbon fiber shank and Zoom Air cushioning.

An OG regional release from 2004, the Air Jordan 19 'West Coast' features a premium white leather upper that's sharply contrasted by the silhouette's signature sheath, finished entirely in black patent leather that extends to the toe. A braided sleeve is included in lieu of laces, while a Phylon midsole with double-stacked Zoom Air in the heel and full-length Zoom Air underfoot provides cushioning.

This OG edition of the Air Jordan 19 Low dropped in 2004.The low-top features a white leather upper, free of the signature lace cover of its full-height counterpart. The Tech-Flex woven construction is used on the tongue instead, while the toe wrap is embellished with grey elephant print. A crisp white midsole packs a double-stacked Air sole unit in the heel, along with full-length Zoom Air cushioning.

The Air Jordan 19 SE ‘Black Metallic Gold’ keeps the patent leather toe but ditches the Tech-Flex shroud and lace locks of the original. The rest of the upper is constructed from black full-grain leather, complete with traditional lace closure and metallic gold accents. A matching black phylon midsole packs a carbon fiber shank plate and dual Zoom Air units, double-stacked in the heel.

This Air Jordan 19 Low features a black durabuck upper with a wavy stitch pattern, forgoing the usual shroud and patent leather construction. A silver elephant print overlay accents the toe, while the Jumpman branding, inside of the tongue and outsole all add hits of Varsity Red.

The Air Jordan 19 SE 'East Coast' sports a white leather upper accented with a chrome Jumpman on the lateral collar, released in November 2004 as a regional exclusive. On the lining appears a contrasting Deep Red, with a glossy leather toe in Flint Grey. The tooling of the shoe is constructed with a high-density foam midsole housing in the heel a double-stacked Zoom Air unit.

A regional release from 2004, the Air Jordan 19 SE ‘West Coast’ features a distinctive colorway that immediately calls to mind the Los Angeles Lakers. The mid-top sports a stitched white leather upper with contrasting pops of Varsity Purple on the collar lining and patent leather toe. Metallic gold accents shine on the eyelets and Jumpman logo at the lateral collar.

A regional release alongside East and West colorways, the Air Jordan 19 'Midwest' features red patent leather on the toe and outlining the signature Techflex overlay. The rest of the upper appears in white leather, with a double-stacked Zoom Air unit in the heel and a full-length Zoom Air unit underfoot providing cushioning.

This Air Jordan 19 Low is a lifestyle take on Michael Jordan's 19th signature shoe, featuring a soft suede build in blue. White overlays contrast the design, while the shoe's basketball heritage comes through in the quick-lace system and flex-grooved outsole.

The final OG Regional Release from 2004, the Air Jordan 19 'East Coast' features a distinctive Midnight Navy patent leather overlay that extends from the silhouette's signature sheath onto the toe. A braided sleeve replaces the laces, while a Phylon midsole with double-stacked Zoom Air in the heel and full-length Zoom Air throughout provides cushioning underfoot.

The Air Jordan 23 'UNC' features a familiar color scheme paying tribute to Michael Jordan’s North Carolina alma mater. The shoe’s unique design is dominated by intricate stitch detailing on the black leather side panels, complemented by a metallic blue finish on the sculpted TPU midsole. Personal touches include MJ’s thumb print on the interior tongue and his signature at the toe.

The Air Jordan 23 'Black Stealth’ is an OG colorway of Michael Jordan's 23rd signature shoe, featuring a Chicago Bulls look. The familiar palette emerges on a silhouette that incorporates several personal Michael Jordan touches, including his thumbprint inside the tongue and his autograph on the toe.

Paying tribute to the Windy City, the Air Jordan 23 Retro ‘Chicago’ is modeled after the city forever linked to Michael Jordan. Removing the usual DNA-stitch detailing, the University Red upper emerges with a tumbled leather build accented by gold contrast stitching. ‘Chi' and 'City’ beneath a skyline near the heels call out Chicago, as do the ‘773’ and ‘312’ area codes inside the tongues, while Michael Jordan’s autograph on the toe and an outsole inspired by his fingerprint bring together the city and the icon.

Miami retailer SoleFly joined Jordan Brand to create the SoleFly x Air Jordan 23 ‘Florida Marlins,’ a special-edition Air Jordan 23 finished in the original colors of the now-Miami Marlins. The mid-top’s leather upper sports the Jordan 23’s signature stitch detailing, with Hyper Turquoise coating the entire build. The left shoe replaces the usual ‘23’ with laser-etched SoleFly branding, while a carbon fiber shank plate underfoot provides the only deviation from the monochromatic look.

The Air Jordan 23 Premier ‘Titanium’ launched in 2008 as the silhouette’s debut colorway. Featuring a colorway inspired by Michael Jordan’s North Carolina alma mater, the mid-top was distributed to the top 23 Jordan accounts in both the US and overseas markets, with each retailer receiving just 23 pairs. The resulting 1,058 pairs came with individually numbered hangtags.

A collaboration between Miami's Trophy Room and Jordan Brand, the Trophy Room x Air Jordan 23 'Black' was designed by Michael Jordan's son Marcus. Featuring a unique design that sports Michael Jordan's initials on the upper and his signature on the toe cap, 'Heir Jordan' is written across the inside of the tongues in metallic gold. Supported by a shank plate and white outsole, the shoe was a Trophy Room online-exclusive and limited to 5,000 pairs.

The limited-edition Air Jordan 23 'All-Star' debuted during the 2008 NBA All-Star weekend. Featuring a white upper with the signature stitching pattern throughout, the design emerges in black and Varsity Red. The midsole incorporates an Independent Podular System as well as a carbon fiber plate.

The Air Jordan 23 'Metallic Gold' applies gilded accents to an otherwise neutral color scheme, highlighted by a white leather upper with intricate DNA-inspired stitching on the shoe’s side panels. Contrasting black hits appear on the knit collar and toe, inscribed with MJ’s signature in metallic gold. Performance details include full-length Zoom Air cushioning and a carbon fiber shank plate.

The Air Jordan 23 ‘Chicago’ dropped on Black Friday 2008 alongside ‘UNC’ and ‘Motorsports’ colorways of the Tinker Hatfield-designed silhouette. Intricate DNA-inspired stitching on the shoe’s black leather side panels represents the shoe’s dominant feature, with a white patent leather toe box and red TPU midsole completing the classic Chicago color palette.

The Air Jordan 23 ‘White Varsity Red’ dropped in 2008, showcasing intricate DNA-inspired stitching on the shoe’s white leather side panel. Additional details include Michael Jordan’s signature on the toe, his thumbprint on the interior tongue and a traction pattern on the rubber outsole that brings his fingerprints to life. Finally, the shoe’s sculpted midsole and collar lining are finished in Varsity Red.

The Air Jordan 23 ‘Motorsports’ celebrates Michael Jordan’s motorcycle racing team, featuring side panels adorned with intricate detailing on black leather base. A contrasting white finish is used on a knit collar and perforated patent leather toe box. Personal cues include MJ’s thumb print on the interior tongue and his signature inscribed on the shoe’s black toe wrap.

Limited to just 523 pairs, the Trophy Room x Air Jordan 2 ‘White’ launched in 2016 to mark the grand opening of Marcus Jordan’s sneaker boutique. The mid-top features a white and gold color scheme, with ‘MJ’ embroidery on the side panels and a translucent outsole revealing Trophy Room logo. ‘5’ and ‘23’ appear on the interior tongue of each shoe, a nod to the jersey numbers of Marcus and his father.

This Air Jordan 23 Low presents a lifestyle take on Michael Jordan's 23rd signature shoe. Despite its monochromatic palette, the colorway gets a unique look thanks to the signature DNA-inspired design on the sidewalls, which has been adjusted to fit on the smaller profile. The black patent leather toe cap and mudguard match the TPU midsole, while the traction pattern on the outsole is inspired by Jordan's fingerprint.

Launching in December 2008, the Air Jordan 23 ‘Finale’ was intended to mark the final release of numbered Air Jordan models, at least until Jordan Brand resumed the practice with the Air Jordan 29. The mid-top sports a classic Chicago-inspired colorway, highlighted by elaborate stitch detailing in red and grey on a black nubuck upper. Additional pops of Varsity Red appear on the collar and TPU midsole.

The Air Jordan 23 Low arrives in a classic two-tone color scheme, featuring a white leather upper with the silhouette’s signature DNA-inspired stitching on the side panels. Contrasting hits of Midnight Navy appear on the tongue, heel tab and midsole. Underfoot, the rubber outsole, featuring a traction pattern that replicates MJ’s fingerprint, is fitted with a carbon fiber shank plate.

Fresh for the fall, this Jordan Formula 23 comes in a clean black, sail and gum yellow colorway. Featuring a black-based upper, inspired by the Air Jordan 10 with stretch laces that hug your foot for a secure fit and a molded collar. The mudguard wraps around the shoe and connects to the laces to provide full support. A white lightweight foam midsole and full solid gum rubber outsole finishes things off. Their release date was October 1st, 2017. They were available at select Jordan Brand retailers worldwide for $120 in men's sizes. If you like the classic look of the AJ 10 and prefer modern-day designs, the Jordan Formula 23 is perfect for you. Particularly this colorway, you can't go wrong with black-based kicks, especially ones with a gum sole. Those that have pairs to sell can hit up the marketplace and list them today. If you're looking to buy, you can grab them online now.

The Air Jordan 23 Premier ‘Titanium’ launched in 2008 as the silhouette’s debut colorway. Featuring a colorway inspired by Michael Jordan’s North Carolina alma mater, the mid-top was distributed to the top 23 Jordan accounts in both the US and overseas markets, with each retailer receiving just 23 pairs. The resulting 1,058 pairs came with individually numbered hangtags.

Recalling the 'Thunder' colorway, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Red Thunder', also known as 'Crimson', emerges with similar color-blocking, albeit in a different mix of hues. The shoe's upper is built with a black nubuck base, highlighted by red throughout, including on the molded eyelets and quarter panel. More red marks the midsole, which includes visible Air for cushioning, while a two-tone rubber outsole is included for traction.

Featuring the same color blocking and materials used on the OG 'Military Blue' colorway from 1989 is the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Military Black.' The upper is made with smooth white leather with a forefoot overlay in grey suede. Black accents are on the TPU eyelets, molded heel tab, and the Jumpman logo on the woven tongue tag. It's built on a two-tone polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit under the heel.

Bringing back a 2006 colorway, which released alongside the 'Thunder,' the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Lightning' 2021 features inspiration from Michael Jordan's motorsports team. The shoe's upper is built with nubuck, finished in Tour Yellow and contrasted by the mesh netting and signature wings. Underfoot, a white PU midsole houses visible Air in the heel to provide cushioning, giving way to a herringbone rubber outsole for traction.

Modeled after the Air Jordan 4 'Oreo' from 1999, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'White Oreo' released in May 2021. The shoe's upper emerges with a white tumbled leather construction, with the usual mesh inserts at the quarter panel and vamp. The molded eyelets sport a cement finish, matched underfoot by the polyurethane midsole. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Lightning' 2021 is a grade-school shoe that brings back a 2006 colorway. Built with nubuck, the shoe's upper appears in Tour Yellow, with the molded eyelets and netting contrasting the look in black. The wings, inside of the tongue and heel branding all add grey to the design, as does the rubber outsole, which provides traction underfoot through its herringbone pattern. The white foam midsole anchors the design, with visible Max Air in the heel included for cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'University Blue' looks to Michael Jordan's college days to inform its classic look. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears primarily in University Blue, with cement detailing on the classic wings and heel overlay. Tonal mesh inserts emerge at the vamp and quarter panel, while the tongue tag is designed to look like a jock tag on the bottom hem of Jordan jerseys. Visible Air in the heel of the speckled midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro OG 'Fire Red' 2020 released in 2020, bringing back the OG colorway of the silhouette. The shoe's upper is built with white leather, accented by hits of Fire Red throughout, including the signature eyelets. Underfoot, the midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, while a Nike Air logo on the heel completes the throwback look.

The Wmns Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Shimmer' is a neutral take on the iconic basketball design. The shoe's upper features a leather construction, finished in a series of tan hues and complemented by the quarter panel netting. Molded eyelets secure the fit, while the tongue includes metallic silver Jumpman branding to highlight the look. Underfoot, the midsole houses the usual visible Air in the heel to provide cushioning, giving way to a herringbone rubber outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'University Blue' is a grade-school shoe with a familiar University of North Carolina colorway. As a result, the shoe's upper includes a woven jock tag on the tongue, with the look recalling the labels on throwback Nike basketball jerseys. Otherwise finished primarily in University Blue, the upper includes cement detailing throughout, matched by the midsole underfoot, which houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning.

Transforming the OG colorway with a retooled build designed for the golf course is the Air Jordan 4 Golf 'Bred.' The upper recreates the 1989 original, highlighted by a black nubuck upper with tonal quarter panel netting, grey TPU eyelets, and red Jumpman branding on the woven tongue tag with another Jumpman logo on the molded heel tab. The AJ4's distinctive midsole comes with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel, and a translucent outsole plate has seven removable spikes for better grip.

Featuring a subdued look, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Taupe Haze' released in January 2021. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of textured suede and cracked leather, finished in Taupe Haze and contrasted by the laces, wings and heel overlay. Infrared 23 highlights the tongue branding and inside of the tongue, while underfoot, a two-tone midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, with encapsulated Air in the forefoot. A rubber outsole is included for traction. The usual mesh inserts at the quarter panel and vamp complete the classic look.

Looking to one of Michael Jordan's oldest nicknames, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Black Cat' 2020 brings back a 2006 colorway. Built with suede, the upper appears entirely in black, save for a hit of Light Graphite on the tongue branding. Underfoot, the Air midsole continues the tonal look, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

Released in August 2020, the Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro is a follow-up to an Air Jordan 1 collaboration from 2018. Built with black suede, the upper includes mesh on the toe box and collar. Translucent wings mark the quarter panel, while the classic eyelets appear in black and white. Contrast stitching emerges throughout, while the Air Jordan tongue tag sports an inside-out aesthetic. The side wall includes 'UN/LA' branding, while underfoot, a yellowed midsole contributes to the retro look, with visible Air in the heel providing cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro OG 'Bred' 2019 released to help celebrate the 30th annivesary of the silhouette. Featuring the same OG colorway that Michael Jordan wore while hitting 'The Shot' in 1989, the shoe features a black nubuck upper complemented by hits of Cement Grey. Fire Red accents emerge on the tongue and outsole, while Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The OFF-WHITE x Wmns Air Jordan 4 SP 'Sail' released as part of a collaboration between Virgil Abloh's luxury brand and Jordan Brand. The classic basketball silhouette emerges with a deconstructed leather build, finished in off-white and complemented by semi-translucent TPU on the eyelets, wings and heel panel. A tonal zip-tie and 'Air' above the visible cushioning complete the look.

Updating the classic basketball silhouette for the links, the Air Jordan 4 Golf 'Military Blue' is a performance golf shoe. Built with leather, the shoe's Air Jordan 4 upper includes a series of blue accents throughout, including below the white netting that marks the quarter panel and vamp. The forefoot overlay and structural wings add grey to the look, while underfoot, removable spikes on the outsole plate are included for traction.

Only available in kids sizing is the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Wild Things.' It updates Tinker Hatfield's original design with a cozy build and has an upper crafted from tan leather with tonal fleece construction on the collar and tongue. Molded eyelets are featured in neon green, pink, royal blue, and crimson, with matching colored structural wings. Jumpman branding is on the molded heel tab and woven tongue tag, both rendered in a dark beige finish. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white foam midsole, enhanced with visible Air-sole cushioning and reinforced with grippy gum rubber under the forefoot and heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro PS 'University Blue' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. Featuring a University of North Carolina-style look, the shoe's upper includes a suede construction, finished in University Blue and highlighted by cement detailing that recalls the 'White Cement.' The tongue includes a woven jock tag similiar to the labels on retro Nike basketball jerseys, while visible Air in the midsole underfoot provides cushioning.

Releasing in November 2020, the Air Jordan 4 Retro OG GS 'Fire Red' 2020 brings back an OG colorway. A grade-school shoe, the upper is built leather, finished primarily in white and accented by Fire Red on the eyelets, tongue tag and inner lining. Black offers contrast throughout, while more Fire Red marks the midsole, which includes visible Air in the heel for cushioning.

A collaboration between Jordan Brand and Union LA, the Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Guava Ice' released in 2020 as a follow-up to the brands' joint 2018 effort. Built with pink suede the upper includes mesh at the toe box, quarter panel and collar to provide breathability. The TPU wing sports a semitranslucent finish, while the lateral quarter panel includes a Union LA flag. Underfoot, the yellowed midsole houses visible Max Air in the heel for cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'White Oreo' is a grade-school iteration of the shoe known for 'The Shot.' Appearing here in a neutral colorway, the shoe's upper is built with tumbled leather, finished in white and complemented by Tech Grey throughout, including on the speckled, molded eyelets. The usual mesh inserts mark the quarter panel and vamp, while the tongue adds Fire Red via the Jumpman branding. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning.

Bringing back the 2006 colorway, the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS 'Lightning' 2021 released a decade and a half later, appearing here in preschool sizes. The shoe's nubuck upper appears primarily in Tour Yellow, with dark grey contrasting the wings on the side wall. The eyelets and netting add black for further contrast, while underfoot, the white foam midsole forgoes the usual visible Air in the heel. A grey rubber outsole is included for traction.

The Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Desert Moss' released to celebrate 30 years of the retailer. Bringing back a modified AJ4 created by the two brands in 2020, the shoe's aesthetic is informed by outdoor gear from the 80s and 90s, as noted by its inclusion in the Tent and Trail capsule. Built with a purple mesh base, yellow suede overlays the design, while turquoise on the molded eyelets and heel patch adds further color. Maintaining signature features of its predecessor, the shoe also includes a stitched fold-down tongue, yellow 'UN/LA' tag and translucent TPU wings, while underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the polyurethane midsole provides cushioning.

Released in August 2019 to help celebrate the 30th anniversary of the silhouette, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Cool Grey' 2019 brings back a 2004 colorway. The shoe's nubuck upper appears in Cool Grey, with Dark Charcoal providing a complement on the signature eyelets. The tongue sports a Flight tag with a hit of Varsity Maize, while underfoot, a white midsole houses a visible Air unit in the heel. The rubber outsole underfoot includes a herringbone traction pattern.

Inspired by spacesuits, the Wmns Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Starfish' emerges with a unique construction. The shoe's upper features a black metallic mesh build, with raw edges revealing the Starfish underlays. Black mesh inserts appear at the quarter panel and vamp, with further Starfish on the tongue branding. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

A collaboration between Jordan Brand and Paris Saint-Germain, the Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Bordeaux' emerges with an elevated colorway. Featuring color-blocking modeled after the 'Fire Red,' the shoe's white leather upper includes Bordeaux hits on the eyelets, inner tongue and heel. The heel itself sports Jumpman and PSG branding, while Paname appears on the lateral forefoot tag. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro OG ‘White Cement’ returned to store shelves in 2016, featuring a design that’s true to the original 1989 release. The build makes use of a white leather upper, accented with speckled Cement Grey hits on the shoe’s structural wings, midsole and heel panel, the latter adorned with Nike Air branding. A red Jumpman logo on the woven Flight tongue tag offers a contrasting pop of color.

The Air Jordan 4 PS 'Wild Things' are shoes for little kids and made for colder weather. It has fleece on both the padded collar and Jumpman icon embroidered tongue. The rest of the upper is built with tan leather and a quartet of color-popped eyelets in neon green, pink, blue, and red. An additional Jumpman logo is featured on the molded heel panel in dark beige and its two-tone foam midsole is supported by an outsole built with gum rubber under the forefoot and heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Taupe Haze' is a grade-school shoe with a neutral look. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of textured suede and cracked leather, finished in Taupe Haze and complemented by Oil Grey on the molded eyelets, support wings and heel panel. The tongue tag and tongue lining highlight the look in Infrared 23, while underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Metallic Pack - Court Purple' released as part of the three-shoe Metallic Pack. Built with white leather, the upper includes tonal mesh on the quarter panel and vamp. The look is highlighted by metallic Court Purple on the eyelets, while more Court Purple marks the branding, tongue and Max Air unit in the heel.

Inspired by the OG colorway of the Air Max 95, the Air Jordan 4 Retro LE 'Neon 95' features vibrant accents on its largely neutral costruction. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in a greyscale pattern and highlighted by the eyelets, quarter panel netting and heel branding. Underfoot, more Volt marks the Air unit in the heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Golf 'White Cement' brings the iconic basketball silhouette to the links. Featuring an OG colorway from 1989, the shoe's upper is built with white leather, highlighted by cement detailing on the quarter panel wings, heel overlay and midsole. The midsole itself houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a full-length outsole plate with seven removable spikes for traction on the course.

The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Cactus Jack' honors the rapper’s hometown of Houston. Its palette borrows from the team colors of the city’s former Oilers football team, and features a Durabuck leather upper in University Blue, while its insole and branding are dressed in Varsity Red. Completing the look are a black lace cage and speckled light blue heel panel.

Bringing back color blocking similar to the 2013 release of the 'Green Glow' AJ4 is the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Infrared.' The upper is made from smooth nubuck in a charcoal finish. A lighter shade of grey is on the forefoot overlay with black accents on the quarter panel netting, structural wings, and Jumpman-branded heel tab. The titular hue lights up the woven tongue tag and molded eyelets. It's built on a polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE 'What The 4' combines the silhouette’s four OG colorways on a single pair. The mismatched designs on the left and right shoe both make use of a white leather upper, complete with original details that include a woven flight tongue tag, quarter panel netting, visible Air cushioning on the midsole and Nike Air branding on the heel panel.

Giving the nod to Spike Lee's Do the Right Thing, the Wmns Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Do The Right Thing' features a look inspired by one of the movie's more notable scenes. Modeled after the Air Jordan 4 'White Cement' worn by Buggin' Out, the shoe also draws from the character's custom lacing job. The usual tooling includes visible Air underfoot.

The Air Jordan 4 Winter 'Loyal Blue' brings a winterized build to Michael Jordan's fourth signature shoe. The upper is built with Loyal Blue nubuck, with a fleece inner lining insulating the fit. The shoe's signature eyelet flange remains intact, while underfoot, the white Air midsole provides cushioning and contrast. A herringbone rubber outsole provides traction.

Released in May 2019, the Air Jordan 4 Retro OG GS 'Bred' 2019 pays tribute to the 30th anniversary of the Air Jordan 3. Emerging in the OG colorway that Michael Jordan wore when he hit 'The Shot' in the 1989 playoffs, the shoe's black nubuck upper includes tonal mesh vents, complemented by Cement Grey on the eyelets and lining. Fire Red accents emerge on the tongue branding and outsole, while the midsole houses visible Air in the heel of this grade-school shoe.

Originally released in 1999, the Air Jordan 4 Retro LS 'Oreo' 2015 dropped more than a decade and a half later. Built with tumbled leather, the shoe's upper appears in black, secured by oval laces and replacing its signature netting with perforations on the quarter panel. Speckled detailing accents the signature molded eyelets, matched by the polyurethane midsole underfoot, which houses visible Air for cushioning. A herringbone rubber outsole is included for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'DIY' features a look designed to be customized. The shoe's upper is built with leather, finished in white and contrasted by black throughout, including on the TPU eyelets and structural wings. The vamp includes the usual netting, but the quarter panel forgoes it, instead adding pen-and-ink grapics. Those designs can be filled in using markers, adding color to the look. Underfoot, the lightly speckled midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning.

description: Inspired by Nike's All Conditions Gear line, the Air Jordan 4 Golf NRG 'ACG' brings a vibrant look to the basketball classic, which has been updated for the links. The shoe's upper is built with water-resistant textile in place of the usual leather or nubuck, finished in teal and complemented by purple on the signature netting. Black contrast emerges throughout, while the heel and tongue branding add orange to highlight the look. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a full-length plate with removable spikes for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Lemon Venom' is a grade-school shoe with vibrant accents. Built with a white leather base, the upper sports Lemon Venom and Pink Blast, with the latter color notably on the mesh inserts. Underfoot, the white midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a tonal rubber outsole that provides traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'University Blue' is a toddlers' shoe with a University of North Carolina look. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears primarily in University Blue, with 'White Cement'-style detailing on the wings, heel and midsole adding to the aesthetic. That foam midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole with a herringbone pattern for traction.

Made with the help of Union LA, the Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Taupe Haze' celebrates the retailer's 30th anniversary. Drawing on a 2020 reimagining of the silhouette from the two brands, the shoe features inspiration from outdoor gear from the 80s and 90s. As a result, the shoe released as part of the Tent and Trail capsule, outfitted with a neutral finish on the mesh and suede upper, highlighted by Roma Green on the lower eyelets and heel patch. Blue Fury instead accents the collar lining and stitched fold-down tongue, which is joined by the translucent TPU wings and yellow 'UN/LA' tag in keeping in line with its predecessor. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning, with a rubber outsole offering traction.

Paying tribute to traditional Southern style and inspired by the Kentucky Derby, the Air Jordan 4 Golf NRG 'Seersucker' emerges with a seersucker construction on its upper. Finished in a mix of Sail and Apricot Agate, the shoe's upper maintains signature design features, including quarter panel inserts and structural wings. Underfoot, the midsole houses the usual visible Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a translucent outsole plate with removable spikes to offer grip on the links.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro OG PS 'Fire Red' 2020 is a preschool iteration of the shoe. Released in November 2020, the shoe emerges with an OG colorway, built with a white leather base and tonal netting at the quarter panel and vamp. Black provides conrast, while Fire Red highlights the design. Underfoot, the foam midsole provides cushioning, with the usual visible Air in the heel noticeably absent.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Pure Money' 2017 features its signature subdued colorway, with a white leather upper accented by metallic silver eyelets and heel Jumpman branding. 'Pure $' appears inside the heel tab, while visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

Releasing in September 2019, the women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Mushroom' displays a muted earth-tone colorway on the occasion of the silhouette’s 30th anniversary. The sneaker’s tan suede upper is contrasted by black hits on the laces, midsole and structural wings, while iridescent Jumpman branding at the tongue and heel add subtle pops of color.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Toro Bravo' relased in July 2013, bringing back a colorway that debuted in 2009's Defining Moments pack. Featuring a nubuck upper in Fire Red, the look is complemented by black detailing and Cement Grey on the eyelets, tongue tag and outsole. Visible Air in the white midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Pale Citron' released to help celebrate the 30th anniversary of the iconic silhouette. The shoe's upper is built white leather, with mesh vents for breathability. Contrasted by black on the lining, heel and eyelets, a unique Bright Crimson graphic emerges on the quarter panel flange and midsole. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning, giving way to a multicolor herringbone outsole for traction.

A toddlers' iteration of the shoe, the Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'White Oreo' emerges with a neutral look. The shoe's upper is built with leather, finished in white and maintaining key design features, including netting inserts and structural wings. Tech Grey emerges throughout, including on the speckled midsole underfoot, while the tongue sports a Fire Red Jumpman to add the only color to the look.

The Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Bordeaux' is a grade-school shoe. A collaboration between Paris Saint-Germain and Jordan Brand, the shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, with mesh netting at the quarter panel and vamp providing breathability. Black and Bordeaux add color to the look, while a 'Paname' flag emerges on the forefoot. The heel includes a PSG Jumpman logo, while 'Ici c'est Paris' on the sockliner completes the collaborative look.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Cool Grey' 2019 released as part of the 30th anniversary of the silhouette. The shoe's leather and synthetic upper appears in Cool Grey, with Dark Charcoal on the signature eyelets. Flight branding marks the tongue tag, while underfoot, the contrasting white midsole sports visible Air in the heel for cushioning. A black rubber outsole with a herringbone pattern provides traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro NRG ‘Raptors’ hit stores in 2018, featuring a colorway inspired by the OG Air Jordan 7. Like its predecessor, the mid-top features a black nubuck upper with red and purple accents, the latter hue prominently featured on the shoe’s speckled midsole and Jumpman heel logo. A second Jumpman is embossed on the all-black tongue tag.

Releasing in 2017, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Motorsports Alternate' dropped alongside a primarily white colorway, both drawing from Michael Jordan's motorcycle racing team. Modeled after a very limited 2006 colorway released to members of the team, the shoe's upper appears in black leather, with Matte Silver complementing the molded eyelets, collar lining and heel branding. Game Royal accents the inside of the tongue and tongue tag, while underfoot, more Game Royal marks the rubber outsole. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The release of Air Jordan 4 'Bred' was released in 2012 as part of Nike's Black Friday launch. One of the four initial colors released in 1989, it has the same colorway as its original Black, Red, and Cement Grey counterpart. In 1999 and 2008, as part of the Collezione pack, the Air Jordan 4 was retro'd. Also, it swaps the OG Nike Air branding for a Jumpman logo on the heel in this 2012 retro release.

The Olivia Kim x women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro 'No Cover' dropped in 2019 as part of a retro footwear collection conceived by Nordstrom’s VP of Creative Projects. As Olivia came of age in the ‘90s, it’s no surprise that the assortment features an Air Jordan 4. Inspired by MJ’s ‘Black Cat’ nickname, the sneaker boasts an all-black calf hair upper, complete with Nike Air branding on the heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Tattoo’ returns the classic profile to its 1989 origins as a performance basketball sneaker. The mid-top’s leather upper is completely dressed in a black-and-white basketball print, highlighted by contrasting hits of Fire Red on the molded eyelets and outsole. The Chicago Bulls-influenced color scheme also boasts basic black on the structural wings, quarter-panel netting, and signature Jumpman heel.

The Air Jordan 4 ‘Dunk from Above’ dropped in 2016, featuring a design inspired by Michael Jordan’s aerial game. The mid-top sports a navy leather upper, accented with pops of yellow on the collar lining, molded eyelets and tongue tag. On the heel, a Jumpman logo hit in white matches the netting used on the shoe’s quarter panel. The kicks are finished with a gum rubber outsole for grippy traction.

The Levi's x Air Jordan 4 'Black Denim' overhauls the classic silhouette with the iconic American denim brand's traditional materials and details. Besides the black denim covering the upper and midsole, the shoe is accentuated on the quarter panel with Levi's signature red tab. Another trademark of Levi's – the paper patch 'Two Horses' – is rebranded with a red Jumpman logo and placed on the tongue, featuring a tan color matched by a gum rubber outsole.

Nike introduced their 'Elements Series' in 2013, where they implemented esthetics of inspiration and design from one classic model to another classic style. Mashing up the Air Air Jordan 4 and Air Jordan 11, the 11LAB4 series sees inspiration from the Air Jordan 11 patent leather accents and the Air Jordan 4 silhouette overlays them. The ' Red ' colorway features the Jordan 4 classic model with a bright red all-over monochromatic leather patent finish.

A toddlers' iteration of the shoe, the Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Lightning' 2021 is a reissue of a colorway that originally released 15 years earlier. The shoe's upper is built with nubuck, finished in Tour Yellow, with the quarter panel and vamp adding contrast via black netting. Grey marks the wings to further contrast the design, matched underfoot by the rubber outsole that offers traction. A white foam midsole is included for cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Golf 'Masters Tournament' debuted at the 2021 Masters, where it was worn by Bubba Watson. Sporting accents drawn from the tournament's signature colors, the shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, highlighted by green molded eyelets, with further green on the tongue tag and heel. The textile-lined tongue sports a yellow finish on the interior side, while underfoot, visible Air provides cushioning, with removable spikes on the outsole for traction.

Featuring a subdued colorway, the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS 'White Oreo' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. The retro basketball design emerges with a white leather build on the upper, complemented by Tech Grey on the eyelets and inner lining, matched by the speckled foam midsole. The usual mesh inserts mark the quarter panel and vamp, while underfoot, the look forgoes visible Air in the heel, with a rubber outsole included for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'FIBA' celebrates the international basketball tournament with a color scheme inspired by the US national team. The retro mid-top sports a tumbled leather upper in monochromatic Gym Red, with the netting on the tongue and quarter panel replaced with a unique design that blends the national flags of different countries. Contrasting pops of Obsidian appear on the eyelets and midsole.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Royalty' brings elevated accents and an elevated construction to the classic basketball silhouette. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears in black, overlaid by synthetic leather on the heel and highlighted by metallic gold on the signature eyelets and heel branding. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the contrasting polyurethane midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a herringbone rubber outsole for traction.

A surprise release on the SNKRS app in June 2019, the Air Jordan 4 Retro NRG 'Raptors - Drake Signature' gives the nod to one of Toronto's biggest celebrity fans. Featuring the same colorway as the first 'Raptors' model, the standout feature is the tongue patch, which includes a purple Jumpman and Drake's signature. The upper is built with black nubuck, while University Red and Court Purple throughout complete the team look.

Introduced in January 2019, the Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Laser’ commemorates the iconic silhouette’s 30th anniversary. Laser-etched designs return on this iteration, which features the adornments in subdued tonal style on a full-grain black leather upper. Eye-catching white contrasts appear on the Jumpman emblems that decorate the heel and tongue tag, while a gum rubber outsole promises superior traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Alternate 89’ features a design based on the Chicago Bulls’ white and red home uniform. Released in a January 2016 three-pack alongside an Air Jordan 2 ‘Alternate 89’ and an Air Jordan 5 ‘Alternate 90', the Air Jordan ‘Alternate Collection’ was a program that re-imagined what MJ Player Exclusive colorways would look like for early model Air Jordan sneakers.

The 2012 Military Blue ' Air Jordan 4 is based on the colorway of the 1989 OG. The design combines an upper white leather with accents of Military Blue and Natural Grey. The sneaker also features Jumpman branding on the tongue and heel, released in August 2012.

Originally released as part of the two-shoe Thunder and Lightning pack in 2006, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Thunder' 2012 dropped six years later. The shoe's upper is built with a black nubuck base, highlighted by Tour Yellow on the molded eyelets, quarter panel and tongue lining. Underfoot, more Tour Yellow accents the polyurethane midsole, which includes the usual visible Air in the heel for cushioning. A rubber outsole is included for traction.

Ready for customization with a blank-slate design is the Air Jordan 4 Ready for customization with a blank-slate design is the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS 'DIY.' Made for little kids, the shoe's upper is constructed from white patent leather with black piping and matching hits of black on the eyelets, wings, and collar lining. Jumpman branding is on the tongue and heel tab, with the quarter panel covered in a print that pays respects to MJ's career achievements. Speckled detailing is on the foam midsole, and the outsole is made of a black herringbone-traction rubber.
Released in October 2016, the Air Jordan 4 Premium ' Wheat ' features Ginger's premium leather top, tonal laces, a Air unit, and gum outsole.

Inspired by Japanese sashiko stitching, the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE 'Sashiko' emerges with a textile construction. The upper features a series of abstract prints and decorative embroidery, finished in a mix of Deep Ocean and Sail. The usual mesh inserts mark the quarter panel and vamp, while the tongue includes Fire Red to contrast the look. Underfoot, the Sail midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, with a rubber outsole included for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Metallic Pack - University Red' released as part of the three-shoe Metallic Pack. The shoe's upper is built with white leather, with tonal netting on the quarter panel and vamp. The eyelets accent the look in metallic University Red, with the color also accenting the tongue, branding and visbile Max Air unit in the heel of the midsole.

Part of the three-shoe Metallic Pack, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Metallic Pack - Pine Green' features a two-tone look with an elevated touch. Built with white leather, the upper includes tonal netting on the quarter panel and vamp. The eyelets accent the look in metallic Pine Green, with the color also featured on the tongue, branding and visible Max Air unit in the heel of the midsole.

Bringing back a two-tone palette initially featured on a low-top release from 1988 and later 2017 is the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Navy' also known as 'Brave Blue.' The upper combines blue mesh overlays with a black tumbled leather forefoot and matching black synthetic suede throughout the midfoot and heel. An embroidered blue Jumpman is on the tongue, while the 13's holographic cat eye is on the lateral collar. On the bottom is a panther par outsole equipped with herringbone rubber pods. The Jordan 13 'Navy' will drop on April 30, 2022.

Combining bright accents with the influence of original color-blocking and materials is the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Del Sol.' The white leather upper features dimpled overlays in matching white tumbled leather with a crimson Jumpman logo on the tongue and a green-tinged holographic cat eye on the lateral ankle. Yellow synthetic suede wraps the midfoot, heel, and lightweight Phylon midsole, fitted with Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot and heel. The mid-top is built on a black panther-paw outsole with herringbone rubber pods and a carbon fiber shank plate.

From the same color blocking of the original "Bred' colorway, which Jordan wore on the road throughout the 1998 Playoffs until the Finals, is the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Court Purple.' This mid-top has black mesh overlays throughout the upper built with a blend of black tumbled leather and purple synthetic suede. An embroidered Jumpman branding is on the microfiber tongue, while the classic cat-eye hologram is on the lateral ankle. On the bottom is the panther paw outsole that features herringbone-traction rubber pods for better grip.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Obsidian' features a classic mix of hues on its classic basketball construction. The shoe's upper includes an Obsidian base, overlaid by tumbled white leather and accented by a hologram logo on the ankle. The tongue includes a Dark Powder Blue Jumpman in embroidered fashion, matched underfoot by the herringbone rubber outsole that provides traction. Air in the midsole offers cushioning.

Released in May 2021, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Red Flint' features a look inspired by the 1998 'Flint' colorway. The shoe's upper is defined by the Gym Red accents on the inside of the tongue, collar lining and reflective mesh overlays, replacing the blue of the OG look. The upper itself is built with a white leather base, overlaid by Flint Grey synthetic suede and sporting the usual hologram logo on the ankle. Underfoot, a panther's-paw outsole provides traction.

Bringing a familiar violet palette to Tinker Hatfield's original 1997 design is the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Court Purple.' Available in kid sizes, the shoe is built with tumbled black leather and purple synthetic suede with the upper almost entirely obscured by dimpled black mesh overlays covered in reflective detailing. The 13's holographic cat eye and an embroidered purple Jumpman atop the tongue are its' branding elements. A panther paw outsole features herringbone-traction rubber pods for better grip.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Flint' 2020 released in 2020 with a look pulled from the late 90s. The shoe's signature overlay appears in blue, accented by reflective detailing. The heel sports Flint Grey suede, while a hologram logo stands out on the ankle. Underfoot, the panther's paw midsole houses Air for cushioning, with a herringbone outsole for traction.

Recalling Quentin Richardson's Orlando Magic PE from 2012, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Hyper Royal' features a rich colorway. Built with black tumbled leather, the upper includes Hyper Royal suede, with reflective mesh overlays accenting the look. A hologram logo marks the ankle, while underfoot, the panther's-paw tooling includes a herringbone outsole for traction.

Jordan Brand added a new colorway to their catalog with the Jordan 13 Lucky Green. The Lucky Green colorway is fairly reminiscent of the Jordan 13 Ray Allen PE that surfaced in 2011.

The Jordan 13 Lucky Green features a white leather upper with green suede overlays and 3M piping. A signature Jumpman holographic emblem on the ankle, perforated white leather tongue, and black and white sole add the finishing touches on this 1990s marvel. These sneakers released in September of 2020 and retailed for $190.

Celebrating the commercial holiday is the Air Jordan Retro Low 'Singles Day.' Its unique build features an upper with a black tumbled leather vamp, black synthetic suede paneling, and pale green leather overlays enlivened with geometric stitch detailing. The latter component has a glow-in-the-dark finish on the medial side, with the luminescent properties on the opposite side printed vertically and displaying 'Air Jordan 0023' and '1111 Low.' Matching green accents are featured on the embroidered Jumpman, which sits on the tongue and the 13's signature panther paw outsole, also featuring a glow-in-the-dark treatment.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Chicago' 2017 brought the OG 'Chicago' colorway back to the Jordan 13 silhouette. Featuring a white premium leather upper with quilted overlays, Team Red suede brings color to the heel, midfoot and midsole. Black on the Jumpman branding and sole complete a Chicago Bulls look.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Red Flint' is a grade-school iteration that updates an OG colorway from 1998. The shoe's upper emerges with the same white leather base and Flint Grey synthetic suede overlays, but the reflective mesh overlays, inner tongue and collar lining are finished in Gym Red rather than blue. The usual hologram logo marks the ankle, while underfoot, the panther's-paw outsole incorporates a herringbone pattern for traction.

Bringing to mind the 'Shattered Backboard,' the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Starfish' features vibrant accents. The shoe's tumbled leather upper appears in white, underlaid by orange suede. A hologram logo stands out on the lateral side, while underfoot, the panther's-paw tooling contrasts the look in black, housing Air for cushioning. A herringbone outsole is included for traction.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Chinese New Year' released for the Year of the Rat. As a result, the shoe's signature overlays feature a Chinese coin-style design throughout. The upper itself appears in Pale Ivory and Club Gold, while underfoot, the panther's-paw tooling accents the look in Digital Pink.

Bringing back a color blocking to a scaled-down version of the shoe Jordan wore during his 6th championship run is the Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Del Sol.' White tumbled leather is executed on the forefoot and signature dimpled overlays with yellow synthetic wrapping around the heel and extending to the midfoot. A holographic cat eye and a Crimson Jumpman logo are featured on the tongue with herringbone traction pods on the bottom.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Flint' 2020 brings back an OG colorway from 1998. True to its predecessor, the shoe includes reflective detailing on its signature textile overlays, while the rest of the upper appears in white and Flint Grey. A Carolina Blue Jumpman accents the tongue, while underfoot, the panther's paw midsole provides cushioning via Air.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'He Got Game' 2018 features the colorway famously worn by Denzel Washington in He Got Game. The black upper with white quilted overlays is accented by True Red on the outsole and branding, with the signature hologram logo to faithfully recreate the look. Air in the midsole cushions the throwback design.

Giving the nod to one of Micheal Jordan's lesser-known nicknames, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Black Cat' emerges with a colorway fit for its moniker. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in black and overlaid by mesh, which sports a reflective finish. Rope laces secure the fit, while the usual hologram logo marks the heel. Underfoot, Zoom Air in the forefoot and heel of the phylon midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a herringbone panther's-paw outsole for traction.

Showcasing a familiar palette rendered in OG-inspired color blocking is the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Court Purple.' Made for younger kids, it features reflective textile overlays that dominate the upper, constructed from black leather with contrasting violet suede paneling. A matching purple Jumpman decorates the microfiber tongue, while the 13's holographic cat eye shines on the lateral ankle. The mid-top is built on a panther paw outsole with herringbone-traction rubber pods.

Featuring a look similar to the Air Jordan 1 'Shattered Backboard,' the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Starfish' is a grade-school shoe that released in January 2021. Built with a white tumbled leather base, the shoe's upper is overlaid by Starfish synthetic suede, which is itself overlaid by quilted leather. Underfoot, more suede emerges over the Zoom Air midsole, while a black panther's-paw outsole with a herringbone pattern offers traction.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Obsidian' is a kid's shoe that combines OG-style color blocking with a familiar palette and traditional materials. It has a navy leather base, tonal suede paneling and large stitched leather overlays in a pristine shade of white. The 13's signature holographic emblem is on the lateral collar with a Jumpman icon embroidered in powder blue atop the tongue. The latter hue is repeated on the panther paw outsole, equipped with herringbone-tread rubber pods for game-ready traction.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Island Green' features a simple two-tone design with multiple allusions to jungle predators. In addition to the paw-shaped outsole and ‘cat eye’ ankle jewel inspired by a ferocious panther, the sneaker’s black leather overlay features a crocodile-embossed texture. Pastel Island Green coloring on the suede upper and midsole is the finishing touch.

Part of the Rivals Pack, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Lakers' gives the nod to the first team that Michael Jordan beat in the NBA Finals. The classic basketball shoe sports a white base, including on the quilted overlays, with Court Purple suede on the heel and midfoot. More Court Purple emerges on the midsole, while underfoot, the herringbone outsole includes hits of University Gold to complete the team look.

The Air Jordan 13 'Atmosphere Grey' emerges with a neutral look. The shoe's white leather base is overlaid by quilted tumbled leather in grey, with a lighter grey on the suede panel that runs from the heel to the base of the midfoot. A green hologram logo brings color to the ankle, while the lining and Jumpman branding add contrast in black. Underfoot, the podular Zoom Air midsole gives way to a black panther's paw-inspired outsole.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘CP3 Away’ hit store shelves in 2015, treating Chris Paul’s PE colorway to a retail launch. Inspired by the athlete’s time with the New Orleans Hornets, the colorway reflects the team’s road uniforms, featuring black mesh paneling atop an upper built with tumbled black leather and synthetic suede in Orion Blue. Sunstone pops appear on the outsole and CP3 logo at the tongue.

In 2009, Jordan Brand presented the collection History of Flight with iconic silhouettes retro colorways that were never made accessible to the public. The Air Jordan 13 Retro ' History of Flight ' released for the first time in 2017 features a tumbled white leather top with a matching beaded overlay. The sneaker also displays University Red details on collar and tongue lining and outsole traction-forward, black lacing system details, and panther-inspired branding on the hologram logo.

The 2011 edition of the Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Playoff’ represents the first ever reissue of the classic colorway, worn by Michael Jordan during the ’98 NBA postseason. The mid-top is clad in black synthetic suede, overlaid with tumbled black leather on the toe and quilted side panels. The Chicago-inspired colorway is completed with an outsole rendered in white and Varsity Red.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro gets the classic ‘Wheat’ treatment, executed on an upper that features a soft light-brown hue throughout. A mesh base is overlaid with premium suede construction on the tongue, vamp and signature quilted overlays. The holographic ‘cat eye’ emblem delivers a contrasting shot of color, while the gum rubber outsole maintains the monochromatic theme.

In He Got Game, Jake Shuttlesworth’s white, black and True Red Jordan 13s took a back seat to his attempts to repair his relationship with his son. But here, the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'He Got Game' comes to the forefront. A grade-school edition of the shoe, the simple colorway includes a black base with white quilted overlays, while True Red appears on the branding and signature panther's paw outsole.

Part of the 2015 Doernbecher collection, the Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘DB’ was designed by John Charles, an 11-year-old who has Crohn’s disease. Featuring a black base with a snakeskin-like texture, the silhouette's signature overlays are finished in emerald green patent leather overlays. Volt on the laces and branding add contrast, while details from John's personal life include his soccer number, the seven pills he takes every day to manage his condition and ‘Crohn’s’ on the outsole. Pink accents highlight the stylized collar and the outsole.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro GS ‘Hyper Royal’ launched in 2018, featuring a familiar colorway reminiscent of a PE shoe made for former Jordan athlete Quentin Richardson. The design makes use of the same color blocking found on the OG Chicago colorway, with red swapped out for blue. Details include a white leather upper, signature holographic ‘cat eye,’ and a black paw-shaped outsole.

Available in kid sizes is the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Obsidian.' It updates the classic silhouette in a familiar palette to that of an OG colorway of the Air Jordan 12. The upper has stitched white leather overlays that dominate a blend of navy leather along the forefoot and tonal suede paneling at the midfoot and heel. Branding elements include a powder blue Jumpman embroidered on the tongue and the 13's holographic cat eye on the lateral collar. The feline theme carries on with a panther paw outsole with herringbone-traction rubber pods.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Hyper Royal' is a grade-school shoe with a two-tone look. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of leather and synthetic suede, finished in black and Hyper Royal. Reflective mesh overlays highlight the design, while underfoot, the phylon midsole houses Air for cushioning. The signature panther's-paw outsole includes rubber pods with a herringbone pattern for traction.

Made for older kids is the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Houndstooth.' It gives the retro silhouette a sartorial redesign highlighted by a white leather upper with textile overlays in a grey houndstooth print. The checked pattern makes a repeat appearance on the padded tongue, lined in lavender textile and accented with a matching Jumpman on the exterior side. It also includes metallic silver lace jewels and a silver badge on the lateral collar marked with Jumpman and '23' branding. It's built on a black and white foam midsole, supported by a lavender panther-paw outsole with black herringbone-traction rubber pods.

Reminiscent of the 1998 OG 'Flint' colorway, the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Red Flint' is a preschool shoe with a notable change. Rather than blue, the shoe's white and Flint Grey base, built with leather and suede, is highlighted by Gym Red throughout, including on the reflective mesh overlays that dominate the build. A classic hologram logo marks the collar, while underfoot, the signature panther's-paw outsole anchors the build underfoot.

Released in May 2020, the Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Flint' 2020 brings an OG Air Jordan 13 colorway to toddlers' sizes. The upper maintains the usual features, including textile overlays with reflective detailing. The hologram logo remains intact on the collar, but the tooling underfoot fogoes the classic panther's paw design.

Featuring a look similar to the 'Black Cat' iteration, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Cap and Gown' stands out with its udpated build. The shoe's monochromatic colorway includes patent leather overlays on its suede base. Underfoot, the panther's paw tooling incorporates Zoom Air for cushioning and a carbon fiber plate for stability. Up top, the signature hologram logo has also been blacked out.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Aurora Green' is a grade-school shoe. Built with suede, the upper is overlaid by white leather, accented by hits of color on the stitched detailing. The usual hologram logo is replaced by an embroidered logo patch, while underfoot, the panther's-paw outsole houses Air for cushioning. A herringbone outsole is included for traction.

Borrowing from the colorway of Quentin Richardson’s AJ 13 Players Exclusive sneaker, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Hyper Royal' boasts a full-grain white leather upper highlighted by suede detailing that wraps around the heel and midsole and is dressed in rich royal blue. Completing the look is a black rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Squadron’ features a nearly monochromatic blue finish on the upper, built with a combination of suede, tumbled leather and quilted mesh, the latter utilized on asymmetrical overlays on either side of the mid-top silhouette. Contrasting pops of Electric Yellow appear on the collar lining, rubber outsole and embroidered Jumpman on the tongue.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro GS ‘Black Cat’ features a triple-black finish inspired by one of Michael Jordan’s early nicknames. The black synthetic suede upper is accented by 3M reflective detailing on the rope laces and mesh overlays, good for added visibility in low-light conditions. The mid-top’s signature holographic ‘cat eye’ on the lateral heel offers the silhouette’s lone pop of contrasting color.

The 2017 edition of the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Bred' brings back the classic OG colorway from 1998. This reissue is faithful to the original, featuring 3M reflective mesh overlays atop an upper built with a combination of black tumbled leather and red synthetic suede. Additional hits of True Red appear on the midsole and Jumpman logo embroidered on the tongue.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Reverse He Got Game' takes a colorway drawn from Spike Lee's 1998 film and flips the color blocking. The shoe's upper sports black on the toe and tumbled leather overlays, with white on the midfoot and heel. A hologram logo adds color to the look, while underfoot, the panther's-paw midsole houses Air for cushioning.

Applying a familiar color palette to a condensed version of the classic silhouette initially released in 1997 is the Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Obsidian.' Its' upper has a navy leather base with tonal suede paneling and white leather overlays that are marked with circular stitch detailing. A powder blue embroidered Jumpman is seen on the tongue while the 13's holographic cat eye stands out on the lateral collar with a rubber herringbone-traction podded underfoot.

Also known as the 'Playground,' the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'KSA' features a vibrant mismatched look. Both uppers feature a white leather base, with the left shoe accented by green and yellow and the right highlighted by orange and purple. Underfoot, the panther's-paw midsole and herringbone outsole support this grade-school shoe.

The 2017 edition of the Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Altitude’ brings back the coveted colorway from 2005. The design is true to the original, featuring premium black leather construction with sting ray-inspired detailing in matching black. Altitude Green accents provide subtle hits of contrasting color on the rubber outsole and embroidered Jumpman branding atop the tongue.

Originally slated for a release in 1998, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Grey Toe' was the sample sneaker for the Air Jordan 13 'Chicago.' Finally dropping in 2014, the shoe emerges with a Cement Grey leather toe and suede tongue complemented by True Red on the heel and midsole. The quilted white overlays are made with tumbled leather.

Recalling the Air Jordan 1 'Shattered Backboard,' the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Starfish' is a preschool shoe. Built with leather and suede, the shoe's upper appears in white and Starfish, with the signature quilted leather overlaying the side wall. Black on the inner lining provides contrast, while underfoot, a panther's-paw outsole anchors the build. Unlike its full-size counterparts, this iteration forgoes Zoom Air and a carbon-fiber spring plate.

The 2013 edition of the Air Jordan 13 ‘He Got Game’ brings back on OG colorway named after the shoe’s appearance in the 1998 Spike Lee film of the same name. True to the original, the mid-top carries a white and black leather upper, complete with a holographic ‘cat eye’ on the lateral heel and paw-shaped outsole underfoot. Technical benefits include Zoom Air cushioning and a carbon fiber plate for stability.

Jordan Brand released the Air Jordan 1 Retro 'Barons' and an Air Jordan 9 'Barons' in 2014 as part of a Jordan-inspired Barons pack. A re-imagined Air Jordan 13 was released six months after the Barons Pack hit shelves. The first Air Jordan 13 to feature a patent mudguard, its Wolf Grey components attract comparisons to the Grey Toe Air Jordan 13 from 2005.

Joining a small set of Air Jordans with an 'Olive' colorway, this Air Jordan 13 marks the first time the treatment is received by a shoe other than the Air Jordan 9. The remainder of the upper part consists of black suede with the signature color on the base, heel and knee hologram. True Red Jumpman tongue branding offers a pop that also appears on the outsole.

While the Air Jordan 13 originally launched in 1997 in various Chicago-inspired colorways, the shoe’s OG low-top colorways told a different story. One of those low-tops was reissued in 2017, featuring an upper that combines black leather and suede construction with a mesh overlay in Brave Blue, treated with reflective detailing for added visibility in low-light conditions.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Lucky Green' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. The upper is built with white tumbled leather, with the signature dimpled overlays highlighted by synthetic suede underlays finished in Lucky Green. Black contrasts the inner lining, while the signature hologram logo stands out on the side wall. Underfoot, the panther's-paw outsole includes a herringbone pattern for traction.

The Air Jordan 13, designed by Tinker Hatfield, features an outsole based on the paw of a panther and an eye-inspired ankle hologram. This 2004 version of 'Wheat' comes with a soft white leather on the toe and a tumbled leather overlay with dimpled detail. It also features an application of Wheat-hued durabuck wrapping around the heel and down on the midsole. The shoe combines Zoom Air with a modified traction pattern of the herringbone.

The 2013 edition of the Air Jordan 13 ‘He Got Game’ brings back on OG colorway named after the shoe’s appearance in the 1998 Spike Lee film of the same name. True to the original, the mid-top carries a white and black leather upper, complete with a holographic ‘cat eye’ on the lateral heel and paw-shaped outsole underfoot. Technical benefits include Zoom Air cushioning and a carbon fiber plate for stability.

The Love and Respect pack has been named in honor of MJ's passion for basketball. Two shoes, a women's size black design and this mainly white colorway for males were included in the 2017 collection. The sneaker features overlays of tumbled leather and lettering of red ' LOVE ' and ' RESPECT ' at the lace bottom. The creed also marks the back of the shoe, dotting the phrases above the midsole and on the heel across the black panels.

The Air Jordan Retro 13 PS 'Gold Glitter' is a grade-school iteration of a shoe with vibrant accents. The shoe's upper emerges with a black leather base, with tonal quilted overlays on the side wall. The heel and midfoot highlight the look in metallic gold, with the classic hologram logo at the heel. Underfoot, the rim of the outsole includes further speckled detailing, and a herringbone pattern offers traction.

Part of the first ever retro run of the Air Jordan 13, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Grey Toe' 2004 released in 2004. Featuring a Team Red upper with white quilted overlays, the shoe's defining feature is the Flint Grey toe. The classic hologram logo adds an additional touch of color to the ankle, with Air in the midsole for cushioning.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Melo Class of 2002’ hails Carmelo Anthony’s high school alma mater, the national basketball powerhouse Oak Hill Academy. The sneaker’s upper, a mix of nylon, leather, and suede, is finished in black, University Gold, and University Red in honor of the school’s colors. Inside, the right shoe sockliner is printed with ‘Class of 2002,’ while the left displays Melo’s personal logo. This Air Jordan 13 Retro is a Nike Factory B-Grade with minor cosmetic flaws.

A grade-school exclusive, the Air Jordan 13 Retro Low GS 'Very Berry' features a contrasting look. Sporting a black base, the shoe's upper is built with leather on the toe and synthetic suede at the midfoot and heel, with stitched leather overlays highlighting the design in Very Berry. More Very Berry marks the Jumpman branding, while underfoot, a phylon midosle gives way to a panthers'-paw outsole for traction.

Calling to mind the OG 'Flint' colorway from 1998, the Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Red Flint' emerges in toddlers' sizes. However, rather than blue, the upper is highlighted by Gym Red on inside of the tongue, collar lining and reflective mesh overlays. Otherwise built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in white, overlaid by Flint Grey synthetic suede. The usual hologram logo marks the ankle, while underfoot, a two-tone rubber cupsole anchors the build.

A preschool shoe, the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Flint' 2020 features a look that originally debuted in 1998. Featuring a white and Flint Grey base, the upper is overlaid by navy textile that also sports reflective detailing. A Carolina Blue Jumpman accents the tongue, while underfoot, the panther's paw midsole houses Air for cushioning.

Recalling Ray Allen's 2011 PE, the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Lucky Green' is a grade-school shoe. The shoe's upper features a Lucky Green suede base, overlaid by white tumbled leather. Black contrasts the inner lining, matched by the panther's-paw outsole. Zoom Air in the midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Dirty Bred’ offers a subtly different take on the OG 1998 colorway in black and True Red. The mid-top’s predominantly black leather upper is embellished with quilted overlays in matching black, along with a holographic green ‘cate eye’ on the lateral heel and a red Jumpman atop the tongue. The kicks are finished with additional hits of red on the midsole.
Released in 2015 as a low-top iteration of the original, the Air Jordan 13 Retro Low 'Bred' swaps the back hologram for a championship-inspired, gold Jumpman detail.

Originally released in 1997, the OG Air Jordan 13 lineup featured six initial colorways, four of which were Bulls-themed (' Black Toe, ' ' Playoffs, ' ' Chicago, ' and ' Bred. '), two blue-shaded (' Flint ' and ' Navy ') and ' Chutney ' color standing out. The Air Jordan 13 ' Chutney ' marked the start of Brand Jordan's more resolute lifestyle color schemes.

Originally released in 1997, the Air Jordan 13 'Bred' would not see its first retro until 2004, along with six other colorways. In 2013 and then again in 2017, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Bred' returned to racks. Inspired by the nickname 'Black Cat' by Michael Jordan, the Air Jordan 13 sole imitates a panther's paw print and heel and outsole holograms depict a cat's glowing eyes.

Featuring a look similar to Quentin Richardson's 2011-12 Orlando Magic PE, the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Hyper Royal' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. The shoe's upper is built with black tumbed leather, highlighted by Hyper Royal synthetic suede and overlaid by reflective mesh. The two-tone look continues onto the midsole underfoot, which gives way to a panther's-paw outsole with a herringbone pattern for traction.

Featuring a classic Jordan Brand mix of hues, the Air Jordan 13 Retro Low PS 'Very Berry' is a preschool shoe. Built with a mix of leather and synthetic suede, the upper is overlaid by dimpled leather, finished in a mix of black and Very Berry. More Very Berry marks the branding, while underfoot, a contrasting white midsole gives way to a Very Berry outsole with a herringbone pattern for traction.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Reflective Silver’ showcases a material that made its first appearance in the Jordan franchise on the tongue of the 5. This time around, the 13’s forefoot and quilted overlays are treated with a silver reflective coating, while the heel, midsole and tongue are finished in black. Pops of bright Infrared appear on the Jumpman logo on the tongue and the rubber outsole underfoot.

A toddlers' shoe, the Air Jordan 13 Retro Low TD 'Very Berry' features a classic mix of hues. Built with a combination of leather and synthetic suede, the shoe's upper appears in black, overlaid by dimpled leather in Very Berry. The same finish marks the branding, while underfoot, the tooling adds contrast in white, with herringbone pods on the rubber outsole included for traction.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Singles Day’ dropped in 2016 on November 11, a date that’s celebrated in China as a shopping holiday reserved for single people. The Asian-exclusive release features a predominantly red upper in tumbled leather and suede, embellished with solid black paneling that eventually wears away to reveal a panda camo print underneath.

An OG colorway of Michael Jordan’s second to last shoe with the Chicago Bulls, the Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Cherry’ 2010 was the first retro of the model. Although the shoe emerges with a ‘Bred’ look, most of the upper is white, with Varsity Red on the suede mudguard as well as the midsole and heel. Black on the outsole and branding finishes off the familiar colorway.

The Air Jordan Retro 13 GS 'Gold Glitter' is a grade-school iteration of the shoe. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears primarily in black, including on the quilted overlay that marks the side wall. The heel, collar and midfoot highlight the look via metallic gold speckling, with a hologram logo near the collar adding further color. Underfoot, the rubber outsole includes further speckling to complete the look.

The CLOT x Air Jordan 13 Low 'Terracotta' pays respect to the ancient Terracotta Warrior statues of China's Shaanxi Province. The low-top’s suede upper employs a padded build that mirrors the warriors’ armor, while the subdued colorway reflects the sculptures' oxidized terracotta material. Gold foil CLOT and Jumpman emblems stand out on the shoe’s tongue and lateral heel.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Starfish' is a toddlers' iteration of the shoe. Recalling the Air Jordan 1 'Shattered Backboard,' the shoe's upper emerges in a mix of white and Starfish, with the leather and suede construction overlaid by quilted leather on the side wall. Black contrast marks the inner lining and is matched by the tooling, which includes a panther's-paw outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro Low ‘Pure Money’ features the the brilliant color scheme borrowed from the Air Jordan 4 of the same name. The upper combines tumbled white leather with suede paneling in Pure Platinum, with a metallic silver Jumpman replacing the traditional ‘cat eye’ hologram on its full-sized counterpart. Herringbone patterns on the panther-paw outsole delivers enhanced traction underfoot.

The Air Jordan 13 Low ‘Hornets’ pays tribute to the NBA franchise that’s now immediately associated with the basketball great. The low-top sports a synthetic suede base in Midnight Navy, contrasted by white leather overlays and a metallic silver Jumpman on the lateral heel. It all rides on a signature panther paw outsole in turquoise.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Lakers' released as part of the Rivals Pack in July 2019. Paying tribute to Michael Jordan's first NBA title, which came against the Los Angeles Lakers, the shoe sports a white leather base, including on the quilted overlays. The suede around the heel and midfoot emerges with a Court Purple finish, while University Gold emerges on the herringbone outsole to complete the team look on this grade-school shoe.

Jordan Brand prepared an exclusive version of the Air Jordan 13 Low, drawing from Nike's annual Quai 54 streetball tournament in Paris. Equipped with an all-black design, the shoe has a pointed application on the upper mesh, while a number of geometric shapes line the leather mudguard. The shoe also shows Quai 54 branding on the tongue as the final reference to the basketball contest, complemented by a gum outsole for a premium finish.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Flint' 2010 was the third release of the 'Flint' colroway, but it forgoes the 3M reflective detailing of its 1998 and 2005 predecessors. The rest of the shoe features the familiar mix of University Blue and French Blue, along with Flint Grey and white. Air in the midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Lucky Green' is a toddlers' shoe with a vibrant look. Built with white tumbled leather, the upper is underlaid by Lucky Green synthetic suede, complemented by a classic hologram logo. A black Jumpman is embroidered on the tongue, while underfoot, an all-black sole unit provides cushioning and traction.

Originally released in 1997, the Air Jordan 13 'Bred' would not see its first retro until 2004, along with six other colorways. In 2013 and then again in 2017, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Bred' returned to racks. Inspired by the nickname 'Black Cat' by Michael Jordan, the Air Jordan 13 sole imitates a panther's paw print and heel and outsole holograms depict a cat's glowing eyes.

Though best known for its association with the Air Jordan 9, here, the fan-favorite ‘Olive’ colorway graces this AJ 13 Retro. Released in January 2018, the grade school-sized sneaker swaps out the silhouette’s traditional leather and mesh materials for a premium suede upper, and sports Light Olive accents at the midsole and heel. True Red Air Jordan branding completes the look.

Featuring the same color blocking at the 1997 'Bred,' the Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Hyper Royal' emerges with a more subdued look. The shoe's upper appears in a two-tone mix of black and Hyper Royal, overlaid by reflective mesh on the side wall. The collar includes the classic hologram logo, while underfoot, the tooling continues the two-tone look, with a herringbone outsole providing traction.
