Bringing back the mid-top that Michael wore during his 1997 championship campaign is the 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Playoff.' It features an essential two-tone color scheme, featuring radiating stitched lines on the black leather upper and lizard-textured overlays in a contrasting white finish. Metallic silver eyelets are molded on, while color-popped crimson accents land on the Jumpman-embroidered tongue and webbing heel loop. Full-length Zoom Air cushioning is underneath with a carbon fiber shank plate and a rubber outsole with herringbone traction pods under the forefoot and heel.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Royalty' brings a luxe look to its classic basketball construction. The shoe's upper is built with tumbled leather, finished primarily in white and contrasted by black on the basketball-textured mudguard. The classic radiating stitching remains intact, while the upper eyelets, TPU insert and branding add metallic gold to the look. Underfoot, full-length Zoom Air provides cushioning, working with a carbon-fiber plate for stability and a herringbone rubber outsole for traction.

Available for grade school sizes, the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Royalty' features a new take on the shoe's original 'Taxi' colorway from 1996. The mid-top features a stitched white leather upper with black lizard-textured mudguards and metallic gold eyelets. The tongue features matching gilded accents on the embroidered Jumpman logo and a small overlay on the lateral side with debossed 'Jumpman' lettering. It has a phylon midsole, full-length Zoom Air unit, and carbon fiber shank plate. It's built on a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 12 Utility 'Grind' brings a subdued colorway to its classic basketball construction. The shoe's upper is built with a tumbled leather base, finished in black and overlaid by tonal suede. The classic basketball texture appears solely on the phlyon midsole, while hits of Bright Crimson bring color to the branding and midfoot. Zoom Air provides cushioning, and the speckled rubber outsole denotes the use of at least 3% Nike Grind.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Twist' features just enough color to create a Chicago Bulls colorway. Built with tumbled leather, the shoe's upper appears primarily in white, with a tonal basketball-textured mudguard maintaining a signature feature. The molded eyelets and midfoot insert add University Red, while the inner lining, tongue and heel pull-loop contrast the design in black. Underfoot, full-length Zoom Air provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Reverse Flu Game' takes the iconic 'Flu Game' colorway and flips its blocking. Built with suede, the upper appears in Varsity Red, with stitched detailing modeled after Japan's Rising Sun Flag. A reptilian overlay contrasts the forefoot, while Air underfoot provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Dark Concord’ is built with black suede, highlighted by Dark Concord accents on the side Jumpman badge on the side profile and lace loops. Underfoot, Zoom Air cushioning works with a carbon fiber midsole plate to provide cushioning and stability.

Featuring a look reminiscent of Gary Payton's 'Away' PE from his time with the Los Angeles Lakers, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'University Gold' released in 2020. Built with black tumbled leather, the upper includes the usual stitched detailing. The signature mudguard contrasts the look in University Gold, while Zoom Air underfoot provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Indigo' brings a two-tone look to its classic construction. The shoe's leather upper sports stitching drawn from Japan's Rising Sun Flag, finished in Stone Blue and complemented by Legend Blue on the heel patch and tongue Jumpman branding. The mudguard forgoes the usual basketball texture, while underfoot, a carbon fiber shank and herringbone outsole support the fit.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Arctic Pink' brings a distressed finish to grade-school sizes. The design emerges throughout the cracked suede upper, with the abstract pattern contrasted by synthetic white leather on the mudguard. The heel pull-loop, molded eyelets, inner lining and tongue branding add a more vibrant pink to the look, while underfoot, the phylon midsole works with a shank plate for cushioning and stability. A herringbone pattern on the outsole offers traction.

Releasing in February 2021 to celebrate the NFL's season finale, the Air Jordan 12 Retro Low SE ‘Super Bowl’ emerges with a festive colorway. Built with black textile, the shoe's upper is highlighted by a multicolor confetti print on the collar lining and inside of the tongue. The signature basketball-textured mudguard appears in Varsity Red, while the midfoot overlay and molded eyelets accent the look in metallic gold. The heel patch appears in a Tamba Bay Buccaneers mix of red and orange as a nod to that year's host city.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Reverse Taxi' offers a design twist on the silhouette’s OG white and black colorway. The retro mid-top features stitched black suede on the upper, accented with metallic gold eyelets and a red embroidered Jumpman on the tongue. Matching black textured overlays give way to a contrasting white outsole, embellished with a red ‘23’ on the heel.

The Air Jordan 12 Utility GS 'Grind' is a grade-school shoe with a sustainable construction. The shoe's upper is built with tumbled leather, finished in black and sporting stitched detailing throughout. Tonal nubuck further supports the fit, while the midfoot and branding highlight the design in Bright Crimson. A heel pull-loop is included for easy on and off, while underfoot, full-length Zoom Air offers cushioning. Three percent Nike Grind is incorporated on the rubber outsole, which provides traction.

Releasing for the springtime holiday, the Air Jordan 12 Retro Low 'Easter' brings vibrant accents to its low-top construction. The shoe's stitched leather upper appears in white, with tonal tumbled leather making up the mudguard. The upper eyelets and quarter panel insert highlight the look with iridescent hits, while a contrasting heel pull-loop offers easy on and off. Underfoot, herringbone pods on the translucent rubber outsole provide traction.

The 2016 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Flu Game’ brings back the shoe that Michael Jordan wore in Game 5 of the 1997 NBA Finals. Despite suffering flu-like symptoms, MJ would go on to score 38 points in a winning effort that gave the Bulls a 3-2 series edge over the Utah Jazz. This reissue is true to the original, featuring a black leather upper with contrasting Varsity Red on the mudguard and outsole.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Reverse Flu Game' takes the iconic Jordan colorway and flips its color-blocking. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in Varsity Red and contrasted by a basketball-textured overlay in black. A carbon fiber shank supports the fit, while underfoot, the midsole includes Air in the heel in place of the usual full-length Zoom Air.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Bordeaux' puts Jordan Brand's rich Bordeaux hue on an elevated build. The shoe's Rising Sun Flag upper is finished in suede, with a tonal basketball-textured mudguard. The midsole and outsole appear in contrasting Sail, supported by Zoom Air. A carbon fiber shank is visible underfoot.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Twist' is a grade-school iteration of a shoe inspired by the 1997 OG 'Cherry' colorway. Built with stitched tumbled leather, the shoe's upper appears in white, overlaid by a tonal basketball-textured mudguard. The upper eyelets and midfoot overlay add University Red to the look, while black contrasts the look throughout, including the heel pull-loop, which provides easy on and off. Underfoot, a phylon midsole with Air in the heel provides cushioning, giving way to herringbone pods on the outsole for traction.

Made for young kids, the Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'Royalty' resurfaces the two-tone color blocking of the original 'Taxi' colorway. The white tumbled leather upper has radiating stitched lines, supported with black lizard-textured overlays and metallic gold eyelets. On the tongue are matching gold accents in the shape of a Jumpman icon and embroidered 'Two 3' branding. Lightweight cushioning is featured by a Phylon midsole with a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'Twist' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. Emerging with an OG-inspired colorway drawn from the 1997 'Cherry,' the shoe's tumbled leather upper is finished in white, with the usual radiating lines finished tonally. The basketball-textured mudguard also appears in white, whilte University Red highlights the molded upper eyelets. Black contrast emerges throughout, including on the heel pull-loop that provides easy on and off, while underfoot, a foam midsole and herringbone rubber pods provide cushioning and traction.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'French Blue' 2016 brought back one of the more popular non-Chicago Bulls colorways. The white tumbled leather upper features French Blue on the basketball textured mudguard, with the color also emerging on the outsole, where it's compelmented by red. Originally designed as a Washington Wizards look for Michael Jordan, he never wore the shoe on court, as it released after his final retirement.

The 2013 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Taxi’ brings back the iconic OG colorway worn by Michael Jordan during the 1996-97 NBA season. The design is faithful to the original, featuring a stitched white leather upper with metallic gold eyelets and textured black leather overlays. Contrasting pops of yellow appear on the heel loop and carbon fiber shank plate underfoot.

First launched on the Air Jordan 7, Jordan Brand provides it's rich burgundy hue on the Air Jordan 12. A nubuck and suede upper are created more luxurious at the mudguard with a faux caviar leather effect, while Sail components offer some relief to the monochromatic design.

Featuring the same white and black color scheme of the original 'Taxi' release from 1996 is the Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Royalty.' Detailed stitching is featured on the white leather upper with contrasting black mudguards in a subtle lizard texture. A metallic gold Jumpman logo can be seen on the tongue, and the lightweight foam midsole is supported by an outsole made up of herringbone-traction rubber pods under the forefoot and heel.

Featuring a sustainable construction, the Air Jordan 12 Utility PS 'Grind' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. Built with tumbled leather, the shoe's upper appears in black, overlaid by tonal nubuck and complemented by the signature stitched lines. Jumpman branding in Bright Crimson highlights the ballistic mesh tongue, while underfoot, a phylon midsole provides cushioning. The rubber outsole incorporates 3% Nike Grind, made up of recycled scraps from factory floors and used shoes.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'University Gold' is a grade-school shoe that draws from a Gary Payton PE from 2003. Built with black tumbled leather, the upper includes tonal radiating stitching. The basketball-textured mudguard highlights the look in University Gold, matched by the tooling underfoot. Air in the heel provides cushioning, while a midsole plate is included for stability.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Game Royal' dropped September 2019 in a familiar two-tone design that recalls the silhouette’s legendary ‘Flu Game’ colorway. Instead of Varsity Red, this pair sports Game Royal on the forefoot overlays and rubber outsole to contrast the sneaker’s black leather upper. The kicks are finished with Zoom Air cushioning, a first for the Jordan franchise when the 12 debuted in 1996.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Dark Concord' features a two-tone look. The shoe's upper is built with a stitched leather base in black, highlighted by Dark Concord on the midfoot and upper eyelets. A textured mudguard adds to the signature aesthetic, while underfoot, full-length Zoom Air provides cushioning. A carbon fiber shank plate is included for stability.

The 2016 grade-school edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Flu Game’ 2016 brings back the OG colorway famously worn by Michael Jordan in Game 5 of the 1997 NBA Finals, during which His Airness scored 38 points to help give the Bulls a 3-2 edge over the Utah Jazz. The design of the shoe is true to the original, highlighted by a black tumbled leather upper and contrasting red mudguard.

The Air Jordan 12 'Michigan' was originally released as a Michigan exclusive and then released to the public in 2019. Draped in the colors of the University of Michigan, the shoe features an upper molded suede in navy, in contrast to Amarillo's midsole shank accents, upper eyelets, and 23 branding. The two versions are very comparable, but the lining and heel tab have small changes. Finally, to complement the college look, the Michigan logo appears on the tongue.

Michael Jordan’s contract famously included a ‘Love of the Game’ clause that allowed him to play basketball in the offseason, a freedom he used to spend summers promoting the game through basketball clinics throughout the world. The Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘International Flight’ gives the nod to Jordan’s role as an ambassador, releasing as part of an International Flight Collection that celebrated important trips. This shoe recognizes his 1996 trip to Tokyo, featuring a kimono-style print throughout its College Navy suede upper and a koi scale pattern replacing the usual basketball texture on the mudguard. The characters down the heel strip translate to ‘Air Jordan.’

The Black/Varsity Red colorway of the Air Jordan 12 is probably one of the most beloved, earning its nickname from the moment on the hardwood during the 1997 NBA playoffs. The 'Playoffs' are also often connected with the remarkable performance of Michael Jordan in the '97 All-Star game where he scored the first triple-double in All-Star history. The Air Jordan 12 'Playoffs' were retro'd in 2004 and 2012. As the first release to use the Twitter RSVP scheme, the 2012 retro set a milestone for Jordan Brand.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Neoprene' features a classic two-tone look on its retro basketball construction. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of a stitched nylon and synthetic leather, which sports a pebbled finish, appearing entirely in black. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off, while the tongue tag offers the only hit of color in Gym Red. Underfoot, a white phylon midsole with full-length Zoom Air provides cushioning and contrast, with a herringbone pattern on the rubber outsole offering traction.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro Low 'Playoffs' features a look inspired by the shoe Michael Jordan wore during the 1997 NBA Playoffs. The low-top build features a truncated Rising Sun Flag upper in black, contrasted by white on the mudguard and sole unit. The branding and heel patch provide color via hits of Varsity Red.

A collaboration between Drake's OVO and Jordan Brand, the OVO x Air Jordan 12 Retro 'White' was relased via NIKE SNKRS drawings and in-store raffles at the OVO flagship stores in Toronto and Los Angeles. Featuring a white leather upper, a textured faux stringray overlay replaces the usual basketball-textured mudguard. Metallic gold eyelets add a luxe touch.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'FIBA' dropped in August 2019 for that year's FIBA World Cup, held in China. The shoe's channel-stitched tumbled leather appears in white, accented by metallic gold on the upper eyelets, matched by the midfoot shank. The signature mudguard sports subtle national team detailing, while the lining and branding appear in University Red. The heel includes Chinese characters that translate to 'The heart only burns for this purpose' as a nod to the international basketball community.

Inspired by the iconic 1997 'Master' poster by Michael Jordan, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'The Master' features a white-accented black leather upper and metallic gold eyelets. Released in February 2016, ' The Master ' dropped with the Air Jordan 2 Retro ' Wing It ' in a two-pack ' Poster Collection. '

Part of Jordan Brand's 2019 holiday collection, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Dark Grey' emerges with a largely nuetral look. The shoe's nubuck and leather upper appears in white, with grey on the signature basketball-textured mudguard. Gym Red Jumpman branding brings the only color to the look, while underfoot, a midsole plate and herringbone outsole support the fit.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Gym Red' emerges with a Chicago Bulls mix of hues. Built with tumbled leather, the shoe's upper appears in Gym Red, with a metallic finish on the tonal eyelets. A white basketball-textured mudguard contrasts the look while supporting the fit, with black on the inner lining and heel pull-loop. Underfoot, full-length Zoom Air in the phylon midsole provides cushioning, giving way to herringbone pods on the rubber outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'Reverse Flu Game' takes the iconic colorway and flips its color blocking. A preschool shoe, the upper is built with stitched Varsity Red suede in place of the usual leather, overlaid and contrasted by a black basketball-textured mudguard. Air underfoot provides cushioning, giving way to an outsole that incorporates a herringbone pattern for traction.

Landing on store shelves in 2016, the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Deep Royal’ treats the classic Tinker Hatfield design to a monochromatic finish. The mid-top features a premium suede upper and textured leather overlays in the same royal blue hue, while contrasting pops of white appear on the branding hits that adorn the shoe’s tongue, heel and rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Chinese New Year' 2019 features an elevated construction with a unique touch. The shoe's upper emerges with black satin that's designed to tear away and reveal a colorful Bai Jia Yi design, which also appears on the inner lining. A basketball-textured mudguard contrasts the look in Sail, while metallic gold accents the upper eyelets and midfoot shank.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'Arctic Pink' is a preschool shoe. Featuring a series of pink hues, the shoe's stitched upper features a distressed finish throughout its construction, highlighted by the linner lining, heel pull-loop and branding, which add a bolder shade. A white synthetic leather mudguard contrasts the design, while underfoot, the rubber outsole includes a herringbone pattern for traction.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GG 'Vivid Pink' is a girls' shoe with a vibrant look. Built with tumbled leather, the shoe's upper sports a white base, highlighted by Vivid Pink throughout, including on the inner lining and basketball-textured mudguard. A heel pull-loop is included for easy on and off, while underfoot, the rubber outsole includes herringbone pods for traction.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Chinese New Year' dropped in 2017 to kick off the Year of the Rooster. Dressed in color blocking that recalls the silhouette’s OG ‘Taxi’ colorway, the mid-top features a number of unique details, including Chinese characters on the tongue and a faux basket-weave texture on the black leather overlay. Additionally, the shoe’s white leather upper is treated with a 3M reflective finish.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro CP3 'Class of 2003' gives the nod to Chris Paul's high school alma mater, West Forsyth in North Carolina. The shoe's olive upper is built with a mix of nubuck and canvas, with metallic gold eyelets and an embroidered Jumpman on the tongue accenting the look. The sockliner of the left shoe reads 'Class of 2003,' with Chris Paul's personal logo on the right. A Sail midsole contrasts the look underfoot, revealing a two-tone shank plate.

New York's fashion label Public School published the PSNY x Air Jordan 12 Retro in December 2015 as their first Air Jordan collaboration accessible to the public. A collection of 7 pieces of apparel by PSNY designers Dao-Yi Chow and Maxwell Osborn was released alongside the sneakers. The shoe features a leather-aligned insole and gray hangtags that for Air Jordan 12s are not normal. Also the sneakers came in a all black Air Jordan 11 box. The gray ' PSNY ' ultimately followed up in June 2017 with the iterations of ' Wheat, ' ' Olive, ' and ' Bordeaux. '

A follow-up to the Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Gamma Blue,' the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Gamma Blue' features the bright color on its basketball-textured mudguard, midsole and outsole. The shoe's signature Rising Sun Flag upper is finished in black nubuck, with Gym accents on the heel tab, branding and carbon fiber plate underfoot.

Inspired by the iconic 1997 'Master' poster by Michael Jordan, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'The Master' features a white-accented black leather upper and metallic gold eyelets. Released in February 2016, ' The Master ' dropped with the Air Jordan 2 Retro ' Wing It ' in a two-pack ' Poster Collection. '

The 2009 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Cherry’ brings back one of the shoe’s OG colorways from 1997. The design is mostly identical to the original, featuring a stitched white leather upper with contrasting hits of Varsity Red on the mudguard and midsole. The kicks are finished with metallic silver eyelets, ’23’ on the heel and a Jumpman logo embroidered in black atop the tongue.

Part of Nike's 2017 Doernbecher collection, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Doernbecher' was designed by Carissa Navarro, who was born without kidneys. The shoe's simple black upper is highlighted by Pink Blast hits on the upper eyelets, while the vibrant outsoles include personal details underneath, including a picture of her stuffed dog Max, a softball and a basketball. The heels sport her name and her sister's name, while the lace deubré is a slice of pizza.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Sunrise' launched in 2019 as a grade-school exclusive. The sneaker’s unique design accentuates the 12’s signature radiating lines with a gradient blend of pink and orange hues, while the side overlays are rendered in shiny metallic silver. The midsole is finished with a white phylon midsole, fitted with an encapsulated Air sole unit for lightweight cushioning.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GP 'Vivid Pink' showcases identical color blocking used on the silhouette’s OG ‘Taxi’ colorway, with vibrant fuchsia replacing the original black finish on the mudguard, heel and outsole. This preschool edition arrives without metallic eyelets or a stabilizing shank plate, but other traditional elements remain, including the stitched upper and Jumpman branding atop the tongue.

A grade-school exclusive, the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Wolf Grey' emerges with a neutral look. The classic basketball silhouette is built with tumbled leather on the upper, overlaid by a Wolf Grey mudguard and contrasted by black on the eyelets. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off, while underfoot, a carbon-fiber shank plate is included for stability. Herringbone pods on the rubber outsole provide traction.

The Air Jordan Fusion 12 'Playoff' combines renowned heritage Jordan and Nike Basketball offerings to form a hybrid silhouette. The shoe utilizes the midsole and upper of the Air Force 1 Mid while incorporating the classic Rising Sun Flag pattern throughout the nubuck paneling.

The Air Jordan 12 Utility TD 'Grind' is a sustainable toddlers' shoe. Appearing in black, the shoe's upper is built with tumbled leather, overlaid by tonal nubuck and sporting stitched detailing throughout. A heel pull-loop is included for easy on and off, while the tongue adds Bright Crimson Jumpman branding to highlight the design. Underfoot, a foam midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a 3% Nike Grind rubber outsole, which sports a speckled finish and provides traction.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Gym Red’ flaunts an eye-catching rendition of Tinker Hatfield’s 1996 design. The entirety of the mid-top silhouette is dramatically dipped in red, including the rubber tooling and herringbone tread outsole. Contrasting accents of black burst throughout the shoe’s branding elements and sockliner. While the all-red finish presents a revolutionary redesign of the vintage silhouette, the performance benefits stay true to the original, evidenced by full-length Zoom Air that extends from heel to toe.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Arctic Pink' is a toddlers' iteration of the classic basketball silhouette. The shoe's upper features a distressed pink finish throughout its construction, save for the synthetic leather mudguard in off-white. More pink marks the heel pull-loop, collar lining and branding, while underfoot, a white foam sole unit is included for cushioning. The tonal rubber outsole incorporates a herringbone pattern to offer traction.

Released ahead of Super Bowl LV, the Air Jordan 12 Low SE GS 'Super Bowl' emerges with a colorway fit for the occasion. Built with stitched textile, the shoe's upper appears in black, with the signature basketball-textured overlay complementing the design in Varsity Red. The molded eyelets and midfoot accent the look in metallic gold, while the heel patch includes '813' as a nod to the host city of Tampa, Florida.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'University Gold' is a preschool shoe. Built with black tumbled leather, tonal stitching and metal eyelets complement the design. The basketball-textured mudguard accents the look in University Gold, with the same finished on the Air midsole underfoot, which also includes a plate for stability.

Emerging with University of North Carolina accents, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'University Blue' otherwise features a neutral look. The shoe's upper is built with a tumbled leather base, finished in Wolf Grey and contrasted by white on the basketball-textured mudguard. University Blue accents emerge throughout, with Midnight Navy adding further color to the look. Underfoot, a carbon-fiber shank plate and Air midsole anchor the build.

This technical version of the Air Jordan 12 is a 'Triple Black' color scheme that features a ballistic nylon fabric on the quarter panel and nubuck accents along the mudguard, converted into a wintered offering to take on the elements. The shoe also uses a fleece liner for warmth to incorporate a waterproof application.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Reverse Flu Game' is a toddlers' shoe that flips an iconic Jordan Brand look. The shoe's upper emerges with a suede construction in place of the usual leather, finished in Varsity Red and contrasted by black on the basketball-textured mudguard. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off, while a black rubber sole unit anchors the build underfoot.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Dark Grey’ showcases a refined colorway that utilizes a dark grey shade throughout the upper, which is constructed from a blend of stitched suede and textured leather. Metallic gold eyelets stand out against the neutral backdrop, while an additional pop of gold appears on the Jumpman branding at the back of the heel loop. A lighter shade of grey finishes the midsole.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Wool' brings a unique construction to its classic basketball design. The shoe's upper emerges with a wool build, finished in Dark Grey and complemented by black on the signature textured mudguard, built with synthetic leather. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off, while underfoot, the performance tooling includes a Phylon midsole and full-length Zoom Air to provide cushioning. The rubber outsole reveals the carbon-fiber plate that offers stability, with herringbone pods for traction.

The Wmns Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Reptile' is an elevated, women's-exclusive look. The shoe's Rising Sun Flag upper includes reptile-inspired detailing, while metallic gold upper eyelets accent the design. The usual textured mudguard is also accented by a metallic gold insert, while a contrasting white midsole houses Air cushioning and a carbon fiber shank plate, giving way to a herringbone traction pattern.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Game Royal' released in September 2019, featuring the same design and construction as its full-sized counterpart. Details include a black stitched leather upper with textured suede forefoot overlays in Game Royal. The midsole, fitted with Nike Zoom Air cushioning for a plush ride, is supported underfoot by a semi-translucent rubber outsole.

Popular with NBA players during the 2003-2004 season, the ‘French Blue’ was originally designed to be a Washington Wizards-themed shoe for Michael Jordan. However, Jordan retired before ever getting the chance to wear it in a game. This April 2016 Air Jordan 12 Retro BG ‘French Blue’ is a 2016 re-release that brings the shoe to kids’ sizes, maintaining the signature red, white and French Blue scheme.

Giving a premium upgrade to a classic silhouette, the women’s Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Vachetta Tan' boasts a suede upper, embossed leather heel tab, and brushed gold hardware. Even the interior gets enhanced with a quilted aesthetic.

A toddlers' shoe, the Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'University Gold' emerges with a contrasting look. The shoe's upper is built with a black tumbled leather base, with the usual radiating stitching complementing the look. University Gold highlights the mudguard, matched underfoot by the rubber tooling. More University Gold on the branding completes the look.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Wings' released in April 2016 in a limited run of 12,000 pairs. Although it resembles the 'Playoffs' colorway, the shoe's black leather upper is designed to wear away and reveal a gold wing pattern throughout the Rising Sun Flag upper. Complemented by a white mudguard and tooling, the gold midsole branding sports 'Wings,' and the heel strip features a silhouette of Michael Jordan's wingspan from the iconic 1989 poster. Metallic gold upper eyelets complete the luxe look.

The only OG Air Jordan 12 that Michael Jordan never wore on court, the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Obsidian’ 2012 was the colorway's first retro release. The shoe's signature Rising Sun Flag upper is finished in Obsidian, contrasted by a white mudguard and outsole. Metallic silver eyelets add an elevated touch, while hits of University Blue finish off the look.

A collaboration between Jordan Brand and Drake's OVO, the OVO x Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Black' features a black leather upper with textured faux stingray overlays. The outsole reveals metallic gold OVO branding underfoot, while the shoe was originally raffled at OVO flagship stores in Toronto, New York and Los Angeles.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro gets the always popular ‘Cool Grey’ treatment, with the namesake hue applied to the midtop’s stitched nubuck upper and tongue. The silhouette’s prominent mudguard is finished in white, contrasted by an unexpected pop of Team Orange. Additional flashes of orange appear on the shoe’s heel, tongue and rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GG ‘University Blue’ dropped in 2016 as a grade school-exclusive. The colorway echoes the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Melo,’ worn by Carmelo Anthony in 2004 as a member of the Denver Nuggets. The two-tone design makes use of a tumbled leather upper in white, contrasted by pops of University Blue on the collar lining, rubber outsole and various branding elements.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Flu Game' 2009 pays tribute to the famous Flu Game, in which Michael Jordan scored 38 points to lead the Chicago Bulls to victory in Game 5 of the 1997 NBA Finals despite battling flu-like symptoms. The shoe is not an exact replica of the model he wore during the game, with a black suede upper contrasted by a Varsity Red mudguard and outsole. A sick-face icon appears on the tongue as well as the heel, the latter of which also sports '97' and '38.'

Often part of the kids collection, Jordan Brand brought resurfaced the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS with this winterized ‘Triple Black’ colorway in 2018. Garbed entirely in black, the shoe's upper is formed from climate-resistant nylon with robust hardware, boot-style laces, and a large nubuck mudguard. The inside is clad in soft terry cloth for warm comfort while the midsole and outsole are engineered for traction in wet environments.

The Air Jordan 12 Low Retro 'Wolf Grey' features a neutral look on its elevated construction. The upper emerges with a microperforated suede build, finished in Wolf Grey and overlaid by a synthetic leather textured mudugard. The heel and sockliner add yellow to the look via the branding, with a heel pull-loop included for easy on and off. Underfoot, a tonal phylon midsole offers cushioning, working with full-length Zoom Air. A carbon-fiber shank plate offers stability.

The Air Jordan 12 GG ‘Hyper Jade’ is a kids’ exclusive colorway featuring classic two-tone color blocking that stays true to Jordan heritage. The build makes use of stitched black suede, contrasted by bright Hyper Jade on the mid-top’s textured leather overlays and outsole. Details include metallic silver eyelets and subtle grey accents throughout the upper.

The 2009 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Nubuck' brings back a historically significant colorway from 2003, as the shoe dropped in November of that year as Jordan Brand’s first ever online exclusive. As the name suggests, the mid-top features monochromatic black coloring on a soft nubuck build, complemented by matching black overlays and subtle Carolina Blue accents throughout the upper.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Racer Pink' brings a contrasting look to Michael Jordan's 12th signature shoe. The grain leather upper appears in Wolf Grey on the Rising Sun Flag construction, with matte upper eyelets supporting the fit. The signature basketball-textured mudguard emerges with a partially smooth build, finished in Race Pink and white. Underfoot, a Phylon midsole houses a carbon fiber plate and Zoom Air cushioning, giving way to a herringbone traction pattern on the outsole.

Created by the legendary Tinker Hatfield, the Air Jordan XII commemorated one of Michael Jordan’s most successful seasons. This kids' Air Jordan 12 Retro sneaker is distinguished by the unique stitching that gives it a distinctive look, in a uniformly Gym Red textile and leather upper. The lightweight foam and rubber sole continue the Gym Red colorway, while the Jumpman text on the sides and logo on the tongue offer an iconic look.

colorway: Chinese New Year Light Orewood Brown (GS)
description: The Air Jordan 12 Retro GG 'Chinese New Year’ celebrates the lunar holiday with a monochromatic tan finish across the upper. Unique details include faux basket-weave texture on the leather mudguard and pull loop, alongside a subtle woodgrain finish on the eyelets and midfoot overlays. Pops of contrasting red appear on the collar lining and branding elements at the tongue and heel.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro Low ‘Max Orange’ is able to sneak in a bit of color on an otherwise stealthy black design, highlighted by an upper built with stitched suede and textured leather. Max Orange accents appear on the Jumpman logo hits at the tongue and heel loops. They reoccur on a molded overlay atop the quarter panel and the toe of the shoe’s rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Playoff' 2004 is a re-release of a colorway Michael Jordan debuted at the 1997 NBA All-Star Game and wore again in that year’s postseason. Built with a black leather upper inspired by Japan’s Rising Sun Flag, the shoe’s signature basketball-textured mudguard is finished in contrasting white. The midsole and outsole continue the white look, while Varsity Red hits on the outsole and branding tie together a Chicago Bulls theme.

Released in 2015, the Air Jordan 10 ‘Double Nickel’ recreates the look worn by Michael Jordan upon his return to basketball, while the name pays tribute to the 20th anniversary of Jordan dropping 55 points against the New York Knicks at Madison Square Garden. His jersey number at the time, 45, is stitched on the ankle, while the white tumbled leather upper is complemented by black and Varsity Red throughout to complete a Chicago Bulls look.

A highly coveted colorway (that only previously reappeared in 2008 on the Air Jordan 13), ‘Shadow’ returns on the Air Jordan 10. Authentically honoring the original 1994 silhouette, the sneaker boasts an upper of black tumbled leather and Dark Shadow nubuck, plus True Red accents on the heel Jumpman and outsole, and a grey embroidered ‘23’ on the side profile.

The Air Jordan 10 Retro ‘Powder Blue’ 2014 recreates an OG 1994 look, with a black and white tumbled leather upper highlighted by a Dark Powder Blue lining. The non-Chicago Bulls colorway, which released after Michael Jordan's first retirement, also has an outsole that serves as a tribute to Jordan's early career, with Dark Powder Blue on its striped design.

A collaboration between Drake's OVO and Jordan Brand, the OVO x Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Black' released at a pop-up in Los Angeles in April 2015. Featuring an all-black look on the upper, textural variety is provided by the mix of tumbled black leather and stingray textured panels. Underfoot, the translucent outsole reveals 'OVO' branding. The shoe released alongside a corresponding white colorway.

The Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Woodland Camo' features a comprehensive makeover on the silhouette that initially hit stores when MJ had temporarily stepped away from the game. Ditching the traditional leather build, the retro mid-top takes on a ripstop textile upper covered in a woodland camo print. Underfoot, the two-tone rubber outsole lists Michael’s early career milestones.

Debuted in 1995 as part of a five-piece City Pack, the Air Jordan 10 OG in the ‘Orlando’ colorway returned to store shelves in December 2018. The build retains the OG structure, with a white tumbled leather upper accented by black contrasts on the tongue, throat, laces, and midsole. Bursts of royal blue on the collar lining and rubber outsole add the finishing touch to the Orlando Magic’s team colors.

The Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Bulls Over Broadway' helped celebrate 30 years of Jordan Brand. The shoe gives the nod to Michael Jordan scoring 55 points against the New York Knicks at Madison Square Garden after his 1995 return to the NBA. The Gym Red and black upper combine for a familiar 'Bred' look, while the speckled Wolf Grey sole unit includes bars underfoot commemorating Michael Jordan's earlier career achievements. The inside of the tongue sports special Air Jordan embroidery, while '30' is printed on the insole.

The Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Wings' released as part a Jordan Brand collection intended to promote educational opportunities. Built with tumbled white leather, the upper is accented by metallic silver on the mudguard. Green emerges on the collar lining, with mulitcolor piping further accenting the design. Underfoot, an icy translucent rubber outsole provides traction.

Part of the 2016 City Pack, the Air Jordan 10 Retro 'NYC' features a look inspired by the city streets of New York. The black leather upper takes on a multi-material build, while gold on the 'NYC' branding and heel pull-tab adds a touch of color. Underfoot, the classic striated outsole design features alternating gold speckled bars and solid black bars.

An October 2013 release, the Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Steel' 2013 is a retro of an OG 1994 colorway. Featuring a white tumbled leather upper, contrasting black on the eyestay and collar is complemented by Steel Grey accents. The outsole, with its signature bars that highlight Michael Jordan's early career achievements, also features a mix of black and Steel Grey.

The 2012 edition of the Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Chicago' brings back the silhouette’s OG colorway from 1995. The build is mostly true to the original, featuring a white tumbled leather upper with contrasting black hits on the collar, tongue and midsole. Underfoot, the rubber outsole is rendered in black with red stripes, the latter element inscribed with some of Michael’s early career highlights.

The Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Super Bowl LIV' released in January 2020 for that year's Super Bowl, held in Miami. Rather than leather, the shoe's upper is built with canvas, finished in a palm-tree print throughout. Pink and green on the collar and heel pull-loop add to the Miami look, as does the gum rubber outsole with pink stripes underfoot.

Released at a pop-up in Los Angeles in April 2015, the OVO x Air Jordan 10 Retro 'White' features a Summit White upper in a mix of tumbled leather and a stingray texture. Metallic gold accents emerge on the branding, including the 'OVO' visible underneath the speckled midsole. The shoe released alongside a black colorway.

Michael Jordan announced his return to basketball in March 1995 after a brief hiatus to follow his dream of playing baseball with a straightforward statement: "I'm back." The Air Jordan 10 edition commemorates that time. The colorway features an upper white leather with a black tongue and lace on top of a white midsole and outsole. Details include 'I'm Back' on one heel tab with ' 3.18.95 ' on the other, and a list of his achievements on the sole.

The Air Jordan 10 Retro ‘Tinker’ dropped in October 2018 as part of a special collection featuring classic Jordan silhouettes finished in colorways inspired by classic Nike models, all designed by Tinker Hatfield. In this case, the Air Jordan 10 mixes with another Tinker creation from 1994, the Air Huarache Light. The latter’s predomonant blue color scheme, complete with contrasting orange accents, highlights MJ's tenth signature shoe.

Tinker Hatfield and Michael Jordan continued to work together to produce the Air Jordan 10 despite his first retirement. Built with a premium leather upper and a locked-down fit speed-lacing system, the shoe also features lateral stripes throughout the outsole that mark ten of MJ's early career achievements. This colorway borrows from the Air Jordan 4 the cement paint splatter graphic and applies it freely over nearly the entire top.

The 2018 reissue of the Air Jordan 18 Retro ‘Sport Royal’ revives an OG colorway that initially hit store shelves in 2003. Like previous Jordan models, the 18 is inspired by Italian design and luxury sports cars. It features a black suede upper with a removable lace cover for a streamlined look, along with carbon fiber construction on the heel and a royal blue TPU panel atop the midsole.

As the last sneaker Michael Jordan ever laced up on an NBA court, the Air Jordan 18 reappeared in April 2018. And in this ‘Toro’ colorway—meaning ‘bull’ in Spanish—the sneaker seems to reimagine history as if MJ has retired as a Chicago Bull. It boasts a University Red suede upper, with contrasting black accents on the midsole, heel wrap, lining and branding.

When Michael Jordan closed out his history-making NBA career in 2003, he did so as a member of the Washington Wizards and while playing in the Air Jordan 18s. This ‘Royal Blue’ colorway pays tribute to the team’s colors that same year and also draws inspiration from Italian dress shoes and race cars with its one-piece white leather upper, silver eyelets, and Royal Blue inner lining, heel, midsole and shroud detailing.

Air Jordan 18 Retro ‘Orange Suede’ dropped in 2018 as part of a three-piece pack that also include monochromatic suede colorways in Racer Blue and Yellow Ochre. Like its counterparts, the mid-top makes use of a suede upper, featuring an embroidered three-digit number atop the lace cover that represents an internal Nike color code. The kicks are finished with off-white tooling underfoot.

The Air Jordan 18 Retro returned in triumph in September 2018, a representation of the very last shoe Michael Jordan wore in an NBA game. The Racer Blue colorway of this luxurious suede upper reflects one of the silhouette’s chief inspirations—Italian driving shoes—while the translucent white midsole imbues the design with key performance benefits, including double-stacked Zoom Air cushioning and a carbon-fiber shank plate.

The Air Jordan 18 Retro in Yellow Suede dropped in 2018 as part of a three-piece pack, which also features monochromatic Racer Blue and Campfire Orange colorways of the minimalist silhouette. The mid-top maintains the 18’s signature details, including a fold-down shroud, carbon fiber comfort plate and a TPU midsole finished in white.

Created by senior footwear designer Tate Kuerbis the AJ18 is the last model that Michael wore in the NBA. The OG Air Jordan 18 in Black/Sport Royal was released in 2003. Chrome lace tips and eyelets give the shoe a premium look, while a carbon fiber plate and rubber heel wrap take inspiration from auto racing and Italian dress shoes.

One of the OG colorways of the silhouette, the Air Jordan 18 OG 'Varsity Red' features a familiar Varsity Red throughout its luxury-inspired construction. The design, which draws from a Lamborghini Murcielago and Italian dress shoes, is supported by a carbon fiber shank that runs through the midsole. The rubber heel bumper is inspired by race car shoes, while the white premium leather upper features an exterior panel that covers the laces.

The Air Jordan 18 ‘White Sport Royal’ launched in 2003 as one of the silhouette’s OG colorways. Worn by Michael during his final season with the Washington Wizards, the mid-top was designed by Tate Kuerbis, who looked to Italian design and luxury sports cars for inspiration. Those influences can be seen on the shoe’s air vents, carbon fiber shank plate and rubber heel wrap.

The Air Jordan 18 Low forgoes the lacing shroud that's a signature of its high-top counterpart. This model's black leather upper includes a reptilian texture along the eyestay and heel, while the eyelets and Jumpman branding are finished in chrome. Underfoot, a translucent TPU layer overlays the white midsole.

The Air Jordan 18.5 ‘White Black Chrome’ is modeled after the Air Jordan 18 that came before it, but it removes the usual lace cover. The white leather upper features a prominent Jumpman debossed on the ankle, with perforations on the medial side near the toe. The black midsole maintains the build from the Jordan 18, while velour is used on the inner lining. The heel sports ‘.5’ and the heel loop has a Jumpman surrounded by ‘1984’ and ‘2003,’ representing Michael Jordan’s pro career.

The Air Jordan 18.5 appears in a blacked-out colorway, with a nearly monochromatic upper made with leather. A large debossed Jumpman is still featured near the ankle, while a padded collar and tongue are designed for comfort. Chrome eyelets and University Blue details bring the only color to the look.

The Air Jordan 17+ Retro 'Copper' 2016 was the first retro release of the 2002 OG colorway. Also known as the 'Crocs,' the shoe emerges with a white leather upper accented by black faux crocodile detailing on the tongue and heel. Sport Blue accents emerge on the tongue and lace lock, while metallic copper stands out on the branding, eyelets and heel counter.

Marcus Jordan’s Trophy Room linked up with Jordan Brand to release the Trophy Room x Air Jordan 17 Retro ‘Cool Grey,’ a luxe take on Michael Jordan’s 17th signature shoe. The Jordan 17’s usual performance features, including a blow-molded Air unit in the heel, a full-length composite shank plate and a TPU heel stabilizer, remain intact, while the upper now features a grey suede build that also makes its way onto the removable midfoot shroud. Metallic gold makes its way onto the heel counter, with matte gold on the midfoot shroud’s clips.

Jordan Brand collaborated with Miami’s SoleFly for the SoleFly x Air Jordan 17 Retro Low 'Reverse Lightning,’ a 2018 released limited to only 2,300 pairs. Inspired by the Air Jordan 17 Low ‘Lightning’ that Michael Jordan wore during the 2002 NBA All-Star Game, this alternate retro look features the bright Lightning hue more prominently, contrasted by a tumbled leather upper sporting black ostrich-skin foxing on the lace collar. The left shoe has embroidered SF branding on the heel.

Although the silhouette debuted while Michael Jordan was playing for the Washington Wizards, the Air Jordan 17+ Retro 'Bulls' takes on a look inspired by his more famous franchise. Featuring a black premium leather upper, the eyelets, branding, lace lock and heel counter are all finished in Gym Red. The color is also featured on the patent leather heel panel, which is finished with a crocodile print. A white midsole completes the Chicago Bulls look.

The Air Jordan 17 Retro 'Countdown Pack' released in 2008 as part of the Countdown Pack. Featuring an OG black and metallic silver colorway, the shoe's nubuck upper includes a removable lacing cover and a lace toggle. A TPU heel counter supports the fit, with Tuned Air and a full-length shank plate underfoot.

Marcus Jordan’s Trophy Room linked up with Jordan Brand to release the Trophy Room x Air Jordan 17 Retro ‘Cool Grey,’ a luxe take on Michael Jordan’s 17th signature shoe. The Jordan 17’s usual performance features, including a blow-molded Air unit in the heel, a full-length composite shank plate and a TPU heel stabilizer, remain intact, while the upper now features a grey suede build that also makes its way onto the removable midfoot shroud. Metallic gold makes its way onto the heel counter, with matte gold on the midfoot shroud’s clips.

This Air Jordan 17 is from the original production run of 2002, finished in a straightforward white and red colorway. This is the model Michael wore when he returned as a Washington Wizard and packs performance advantages that were new to Jordan Brand. It includes Blow-Molded Air, a full-length shank plate and a heel stabilizer for TPU. The general layout, as seen on the musical notes engraved on the removable midfoot cover, is partly influenced by jazz music. The kicks are packed in a functional briefcase finished in a soft color of red and chrome.

The Air Jordan 17 'Black Metallic Silver' features a simple black look with metallic accents. The full-grain leather upper emerges in black, supported by a midfoot overlay that hides the toggle lacing system. The Lycra collar is designed for comfort, while the TPU heel stabilizer and eyelets provide contrast in metallic silver. A blow-molded Max Air unit in the heel provides cushioning, while a full-length composite shank plate is included for support.

The Air Jordan 17 Low 'Lightning' was memorably worn by Michael Jordan in the 2002 NBA All-Star Game, during which he recorded 8 points and one missed breakaway dunk. Built with a lower-cut profile, the sneaker features a white leather upper with Lightning yellow accents on the midsole and toe. The kicks are finished with gleaming chrome hits on the eyelets and heel counter.

The Air Jordan 17 Low emerges here in a familiar University of North Carolina-style colorway. The white leather upper features tumbled detailing on the overlay and peroforations near the collar, while University Blue appears on the midsole, TPU heel stabilizer, detailing and extended inner sleeve. A lightweight Phylon midsole and full-length shank plate provide support underfoot.

The Air Jordan 17 Low ‘Black Chrome’ converts Michael Jordan’s 17th signature shoe into a low-top, giving it a simple black color scheme highlighted by notable accents. The first is the signature heel counter, which takes on a chrome application that matches the eyelets. The second is the snakeskin design that runs down the eyestay and collar. A blow-molded Max Air unit provides cushioning, while the outsole reveals touches of blue on its traction inserts.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Midnight Navy' 2022 brings back a classic colorway first seen in October 2000. The 2022 reissue stays true to the original, pairing a white leather upper with Midnight Navy hits on the molded tongue and heel tab. The color repeats on the Jumpman-branded lace lock, textile lace guard and back heel. The sneaker is mounted on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, fitted with an Air-sole unit in the heel. A translucent rubber outsole appears underfoot. The Jordan 6 'Midnight Navy' 2022 will drop on May 11, 2022.

Bringing back a 2000 colorway in older kid sizes is the 2022 reissue of the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Midnight Navy.' Keeping the build similar to the original, the white leather upper features perforated detailing throughout the midfoot and padded collar. Navy accents are seen on the molded tongue, spoiler-like heel tab, and the Jumpman branding that decorate the back heel and textile lace guard. It's built on a two-tone polyurethane midsole with an Air-sole unit in the heel and a translucent rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'UNC Home' pays homage to Michael Jordan’s alma mater, bearing a colorway reminiscent of the University of North Carolina. The classic hoops sneakers feature a white leather upper set against University Blue nubuck underlays. Hits of navy appear on the molded TPU heel tab and collar lining. Navy repeats on the midsole, which houses visible Air-sole cushioning. The jock tag on the heel reinforces the shoe’s varsity athletics theme.

The Wmns Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Gold Hoops' brings elevated hits fit for its championship pedigree. Built with tumbled leather, the shoe's upper appears in white, complemented by Barely Rose on the tongue and heel pull-loop. A metallic gold lace lock and earring-inspired gold hoops highlight the design, matched by the attached Jumpman charm. Underfoot, a two-tone midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a milky rubber outsole for traction.

A follow-up to a 2019 collaboration, the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro 'British Khaki' released with the help of the Houston rapper. Built with a mix of suede and canvas, the shoe's upper appears in British Khaki, highlighted by Bright Crimson on the heel pull-loop and tongue branding. The lateral collar includes a stash pouch, with the medial side sporting zippered detailing. The heels include mismatched Air and Cactus Jack branding, and underfoot, the usual visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

Released to celebrate 30 years of the silhouette, the Air Jordan 6 Retro OG 'Carmine' 2021 emerges with a contrasting look. The shoe's upper features a mix of leather and nubuck, finished in white and carmine, with black contrast completing the team look. Underfoot, the midsole houses visible Air in the heel to provide cushioning.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Electric Green’ is defined by a two-tone color scheme that recalls an Oregon PE colorway first seen online in 2018. The classic hoops style features a black nubuck upper with pops of neon green on the tongue and pull tab. An embroidered Jumpman logo appears on the sneaker’s back heel. A polyurethane sole provides lightweight cushioning, fitted with a visible Air sole unit and additional green hits.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Bordeaux' brings an Air Jordan 7 colorway to the Air Jordan 6. Built with nubuck, the shoe's upper appears in a mix of grey and black, highlighted by a translucent tongue with a multicolor print. The throat and molded heel pull-loop add Bordeaux to the design, while perforations throughout and a lace toggle support the fit. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning.

Adding pastel accents to the venerable silhouette that Michael Jordan wore when he clinched his first NBA championship is the women's Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Mint Foam.' The upper's base is a light grey nubuck with white leather overlays throughout the midfoot and heel with an embroidered Jumpman icon in a soft mint green hue. Original details including a molded tongue, spoiler-like heel tab, and Jumpman-branded lace guard are featured with a mint green polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning and translucent rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Infrared' 2019 is a 2019 re-release of the OG colorway. The shoe's black nubuck upper includes a reflective 3M layer, with perforations throughout for breathability. The heel, tongue and lace lock sport Infrared accents, with the color also featured on the signature midsole detailing. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning, while the tranlucent sections continue down onto the outsole for traction.

Originally released in 2006 as part of the Defining Moments Pack, the Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Defining Moments' 2020 dropped in April 2020. Built with nubuck, the upper appears primarily in black, accented by metallic gold. A lace lock supports the fit, as does a cushioned ankle and perforations throughout. Underfoot, the midsole houses visible Zoom Air in the heel for cushioning.

The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Olive' showcases the Houston rapper’s unique take on the classic silhouette. Dressed in military green nubuck, the mid-top features a canvas stash pocket on the lateral collar and glow-in-the-dark translucent outsoles. The kicks are finished with Cactus Jack branding on the lace lock and heel embroidery of the right shoe, both rendered in a vibrant red hue.

Bringing back one of the OG colorways of the 1991 silhouette, the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Carmine' 2021 is a grade-school iteration of the shoe. Released in February 2021, the shoe's upper is built with a nubuck base, finished in Carmine and overlaid by white leather. More Carmine emerges on the lace lock, while black provides contrast on the tongue and heel pull-loop. Underfoot, the Air midsole provides cushioning, giving way to an icy translucent rubber outsole for traction.

Borrowing the OG color scheme from the Air Jordan 7, the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Bordeaux' is made for big kids and has a smooth nubuck upper that combines a grey base with contrasting black overlays, both of which feature perforated detailing that reveals a reflective underlay. Bordeaux accents land on the spoiler-like heel tab and Jumpman-branded lace guard. The jagged multicolor design that distinguishes the Air Jordan 7's neoprene tongue is relocated on the interior tongue and sockliner. Jumpman branding is embroidered on the back heel with lightweight cushioning seen by a visible Air-sole unit in the grey foam midsole and a smoky translucent rubber outsole.

In honor of the lunar holiday is the Air Jordan 6 Low 'Chinese New Year.' The low-top features an ivory-colored leather upper with gilded Jumpman branding on the tongue and back heel. Matching metallic gold accents are on the TPU heel tab and polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel for lightweight cushioning and a rubber outsole.

Jordan Brand paid homage to an old ad campaign classic by releasing the Jordan 6 Retro Hare, now available on StockX. The Hare colorway originally made its debut on an Air Jordan 7 in one of the first Jordan ads that featured Bugs Bunny. Jumpman keeps the tradition alive by transferring this iconic colorway to a new silhouette.

This Jordan 6 consists of a white leather upper with grey underlays and a red detailing. A translucent tongue, patterned outsole, and a purple Jumpman on the heel complete the design. These sneakers released in April of 2020 and retailed for $190.

Made with the help of the Houston rapper, the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro PS 'British Khaki' is a preschool shoe. The shoe's upper features a suede build, finished in British Khaki and accented by Bright Crimson on the tongue and heel pull-loop. Mismatched Nike Air and Cactus Jack logos appear on the heels, while the lateral collar includes a stash pocket and the medial side sports a zippered pouch. Underfoot, the midsole forgoes visible Air, while a semitranslucent rubber outsole is included for traction.

A hybrid sneaker honoring Michael Jordan’s career with the Chicago Bulls, the Jordan 6 Rings 'Concord' fuses together elements from each of the seven shoes MJ wore during his six-time NBA Championship reign. Released in October 2008, the shoe boasts Concord accents, a white tumbled leather upper, black patent panels, and mesh overlays. The rubber outsole and full-length, Zoom Air-equipped Phylon midsole offer responsive comfort and durability.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Infrared' 2019 features an iconic colorway. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of nubuck and synthetic leather, with perforations on the quarter panel and ankle for breathability. Infrared hits accent the lace lock, tongue and heel loop. Underfoot, the Air midsole sports further Infrared detailing, with the translucent detailing continuing down onto the outsole.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Washed Denim' brings a lifestyle look to Michael Jordan's sixth signature shoe. The upper is built with washed denim, finished in two shades, while the signature tongue is overlaid by brown leather. Varsity Red accents the look, while underfoot, the Air midsole gives way to a translucent rubber outsole for traction.

In 1991, the Air Jordan 6 'Infrared' released among five original colorways. Retro releases dropped to commemorate the anniversary of the initial release date of the shoe in 2000, 2010 and 2014. The design features an all-black perforated upper nubuck leather with Infrared accents and a return to the reflective upper underlay, a detail that has not been seen since the initial launch of the shoe.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Red Oreo' showcases a two-tone color scheme. The silhouette features a white leather upper, with perforations throughout for breathability. Crimson Jumpman embroidery decorates the tongue. Contrasting speckled red accents appear on the lace toggle, heel and midsole. An exposed Air-sole unit in the heel provides cushioning, while a translucent rubber outsole offers traction.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Electric Green' is a grade-school shoe with a contrasting look. Redolent of a 2018 Oregon PE, the shoe's upper features a black nubuck construction, highlighted by the Electric Green hits on the lace lock, heel pull-loop and tongue Jumpman branding. Underfoot, more Electric Green accents the polyurethane midsole, which works with visible Air in the heel to provide cushionining. A glow-in-the-dark finish on the translucent rubber outsole completes the look.

First published in 1991, the Air Jordan 6 'Maroon' was the only OG color that never saw a retro release. Nike resurrected this classic in 2015, when the retro was released as part of a huge Holiday drop. The design features branding details including the Jumpman logo on the rubber tongue and lace overlay of the shoe, as well as OG elements on the heel like the Nike Air branding and transparent, translucent outsole.

During the NBA All-Star game, Nike dropped a brand new Air Jordan 6 called the 'Chameleon.' The shoe released alongside a comparable looking Air Jordan 1 and Air Jordan 31. The Air Jordan 6 All-Star 'Chameleon' has an all-black leather upper and a distinctive iridescent color, giving the shoe a color-changing impact depending on the light.

The Jordan 6 Rings 'Black Ice' pays respect to Michael Jordan’s championship excellence by blending seven of Jordan’s championship year shoes. This offering showcases a ballistic mesh upper in black tones with matching patent leather accents on the mudguard and heel. The shoe also boasts a toggle lacing system with an integrated buckle strap, an icy translucent outsole, and a cushioned midsole for support.

The Wmns Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Tech Chrome' brings a subdued look to the silhouette known for being Michael Jordan's first championship shoe. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in black and overlaid by Light Smoke Grey. The forefoot is highlighted by Chrome underlays, while the usual heel pull-tab appears in semitranslucent TPU. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel provides cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Olive' dropped in October 2019, featuring a build that’s identical to its adult-sized counterpart. The mid-top’s nubuck upper is finished in monochromatic olive green, highlighted by perforated inlays and a stash pocket on the collar. Contrasting pops of red appear on the tongue, lace locks and mismatched Nike Air and Cactus Jack branding embroidered on the heels.

In 1991, the Air Jordan 6 'Infrared' released among five original colorways. Retro releases dropped to commemorate the anniversary of the initial release date of the shoe in 2000, 2010 and 2014. The design features an all-white perforated upper nubuck leather with Infrared accents and a return to the reflective upper underlay, a detail that has not been seen since the initial launch of the shoe.

Drawing from the Air Jordan 7 'Hare' colorway that originally dropped in 1992, the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Hare' is a grade-school shoe. Built with perforated grey leather and white leather overlays, colorful accents emerge on the tongue, heel and lace lock. More color emerges on the midsole, which houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning. The translucent tongue reveals a geometric pattern.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro GG 'Citron Tint' is a girls' shoe with a vibrant look. Built with leather, the upper appears in Citron Tint with Dynamic Yellow accents, perforated throughout for breathabilty. The tongue sports an embroidered yellow rose along with black Jumpman branding, with further floral hits on the lining and inside the tongue. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

Inspired by the Bugs Bunny-themed colorway found on the Air Jordan 7 'Hare' and the Air Jordan 6 'Maroon,' this 2017 retro features a base of white and light gray nubuck leather perforated with 'Gym Red' accents all over. 1991 can be discovered stitched on the internal tongue, while the tongue, lace overlay and heel part of Jumpman branding can be discovered.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Jimmy Butler’ is a December 2018 design created to commemorate the Jordan Brand player. The old-school profile features a tonal Diffused Blue finish on the layered nubuck and leather upper and is equipped with a classic lace lock, ventilated inlays and an embroidered Jumpman emblem at the heel. A coordinated Diffused Blue midsole meets up with a translucent rubber outsole.

Featuring the same color-blocking as the iconic Air Jordan 6 'Infrared,' the Air Jordan 6 Retro PS 'Electric Green' brings a different accent color to its preschool construction. Built with nubuck, the shoe's upper appears in black, with perforations throughout offering breathability. Electric Green highlights the tongue Jumpman and spoiler-style heel pull-loop, matched underfoot by the midsole, which forgoes the usual visible Air in the heel.

Iconic French soccer club Paris Saint-Germain teamed up with Jordan brand to create the Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Iron Grey.' The shoe's nubuck upper is finished in black and Iron Grey, with Infrared 23 accents on the Jumpman branding, lace toggle and heel pull-tab. The heel sports a hybrid logo, with 'Paname' appearing on the flag near the ankle. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

Part of the 2019 All-Star collection, the Social Status x Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Pony Hair’ emerges with an elevated construction. The Charlotte retailer puts reptilian underlays and pony hair overlays on the classic silhouette, finished in a minimalist mix of black, silver and Dark Concord. Underfoot, a visible Air unit in the heel provides cushioning, giving way to a translucent outsole for traction.

Released for the Parisian streetball tournament of the same name, the Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Quai 54' emerges with a unique print on its performance construction. Built with leather in Sail, the upper is defined by the geometric design on the textile inlays, while the heels sport mismatched Nike Air and Quai 54 branding. The lace lock and heel add hits of Total Orange, while the Air midsole gives way to a gum rubber outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'UNC' released in December 2017, giving the nod to the University of North Carolina's national title earlier in the year. Featuring a black nubuck upper, University Blue accents appear on the tongue, Jumpman branding, lace toggle, pull tab and signature midsole detailing. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning, while the outsole sports translucent sections.

One of five OG colorways of the shoe in 1991, the Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Sport Blue' 2014 was the colorway's first retro. Part of the Sport Blue pack, the shoe features a white leather upper accented by Sport Blue on the Jumpman branding, heel, midsole detailing, outsole and lace lock. The rubber tongue emerges in black, while Air in the heel provides cushioning.

Released in October 2018, the Air Jordan 6 Retro Trainer SC II stands out as part of a larger collection that takes classic Air Jordan silhouettes and combines them with classic Nike models, all designed by Tinker Hatfield. This Air Jordan 6 features a distinctive white, grey, and Infrared palette typically associated with the Air Trainer SC II, the cross trainer made famous by Bo Jackson and worn off-court by MJ.

Applying a pastel color palette to the legendary model Jordan wore in his first NBA championship is the Air Jordan 6 Retro Low TD 'Atmosphere.' The low-top features a soft pink leather upper with contrasting white leather overlays at the midfoot and heel, which is embellished with a Jumpman icon and a molded pull tab for easy on and off. A second Jumpman logo is featured on the pink translucent rubber outsole.

The 2012 edition of the Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Olympic' brings back the classic colorway first released in 2000. The reissue is mostly true to the original, though this pair adds more navy blue coloring to the midsole. Up top, the white and navy leather upper is accented with red lace locks and matching red Jumpman hits. The patriotic design is supported underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro Low PS 'Atmosphere' is a shoe made for little kids that delivers a pastel colorway of the classic silhouette. A soft pink finish is applied to the leather upper with perforated detailing and bolstered with white leather overlays along the midfoot and heel. Jumpman branding is on the lace guard and back heel in vibrant pops of infrared, which is repeated on the lightweight foam midsole on top of a pink semi-translucent rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Green Abyss' is a grade-school shoe with vibrant accents. The shoe's upper is built with white tumbled leather, underlaid by a printed nylon sleeve in a patterned mix of Green Abyss and Laser Fuchsia. A lace toggle and heel loop support the fit, while underfoot, the midsole includes visible Air cushioning in the heel. A translucent outsole provides traction.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Oreo' features a thematic black and white look that's highlighted by the speckled detailing on the midsole and heel tab. The rest of the shoe is built with a black nubuck upper and white leather overlays. Air in the heel provides cushioning, and the outsole includes translucent inserts.

Nike tapped Travis Scott to create the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'British Khaki,' appearing here in preschool sizes. The shoe's upper is built with British Khaki suede, with Bright Crimson bringing contrast to the canvas tongue and the heel. Perforations throughout provide breathability, while underfoot, a foam midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole that offers traction.

A toddlers' iteration of the shoe, the Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'Electric Green' features 'Infrared'-style color-blocking. The shoe's upper is built with a black nubuck base, with Electric Green accenting the design throughout. A spoiler-like heel pull-loop provides easy on and off, while underfoot, the foam midsole offers cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

Releasing in toddlers' sizes, the Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'Carmine' 2021 brings back an OG colorway. The upper emerges with a leather construction, finished in Carmine on the underlays and white on the overlays, perforated throughout for breathability. Black contrast marks the tongue, inner lining and heel pull-loop, while underfoot, the midsole forgoes visible Air in the heel. The outsole incorporates flex grooves on the forefoot for flexible traction.

Featuring color-blocking redolent of the OG Air Jordan 11, the Jordan 6 Rings 'Concord' emerges with vibrant accents. The shoe's upper is built with ballistic mesh, finished in white and overlaid by black patent leather. Tropical Twist highlights the chenille tongue patch, molded heel pull-loop and rubber outsole, which are, respectively, taken from the Air Jordan 8, 6 and 13. Underfoot, Zoom Air in the forefoot and heel of the full-length phylon midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Gatorade’ draws inspiration from the iconic ‘Be Like Mike’ Gatorade commercial from 1991. The design is reminiscent of the silhouette’s OG ‘Carmine’ colorway, featuring a white leather upper with orange nubuck inlays replacing the dark red of the original. The sport-drink homage is completed with the addition of green accents on the lace locks and Jumpman branding.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Black Cat’ showcases a stealthy design that plays off Michael Jordan’s childhood nickname. The mid-top features a blacked-out leather upper, complete with perforated detailing on the quarter panels and toe. The shoe’s monochromatic treatment is disrupted by white detailing on the midsole and a matching white Jumpman on the rubber outsole.

One of the first colorways to appear on the Jordan 6 Low in 2002, this Air Jordan 6 Retro Low ‘Chrome’ brought the look back in 2015. The all-black upper is built with suede and complemented by the metallic silver Jumpman branding, heel pull-tab and midsole. The chrome lace lock adds another silver hit, while the icy blue translucent outsole adds a little more color than the OG.

Releasing alongside a Jordan 1 and Jordan 13, the Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Wheat’ is a follow-up to the limited edition PSNY x Air Jordan 12. The lifestyle colorway features a premium suede upper finished entirely in Golden Harvest, a signature color that also makes its way down to the midsole. Off-white Sail on the midsole and outsole breaks up the design, while Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Infrared 23' features an upper class Infrared leather with a black midsole, tongue, and heel tab. The sneaker also comes with an icy white translucent outsole, released in February 2014.
The Air Jordan 6 Low 'Infrared' features an Infrared and black accent white leather upper. The low-top silhouette released in July 2015 also features an ice blue translucent outsole.

A kids' shoe, the Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 6 Retro BG 'Iron Grey' continues the partnership between Jordan Brand and French club Paris Saint-Germain. The shoe's upper is built with nubuck, finished in a mix of Iron Grey and black. Infrared 23 accents emerge on the lace lock, 'Paname' flag and Jumpman branding, while co-branding marks the heel. The midsole houses the usual Air for cushioning.

The Jordan Brand's Pinnacle line began with the Air Jordan 1 and Air Jordan 4 silhouettes to introduce luxury and lifestyle aspects to the brand. The Air Jordan 6 received the 'Pinnacle' treatment in 2016 to celebrate Jordan's first NBA Championship's 25th anniversary. The sneaker Air Jordan 6 Retro Pinnacle features a monochromatic bottom covered with gold laces and accents in metallic gold patent leather. Branding elements include the tongue overlay and Jumpman logo, along with a unique metallic gold Jumpman commemorative hangtag.

Drawing from a 1992 Air Jordan 7 colorway that accompanied TV ads featuring Michael Jordan and Bugs Bunny, the Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'Hare' is a toddlers' shoe. Built with leather in white and grey, the upper forgoes the lace lock, while the tooling eschews the visible Air unit. The neoprene tongue with a geometric pattern is drawn directly from the Air Jordan 7.

Styled for growing feet, the Air Jordan 6 Rings GS 'Black' offering is a kids’ version of the hybrid basketball shoe. Created to honor Michael Jordan’s six NBA championships, this mid-top shoe is influenced by each of the Air Jordan models MJ wore while winning his titles. This all-black version flaunts the same ideal as the adult shoe—from the mesh upper and patent mudguard to the Jumpman logo on the tongue and heel. A two-tone cushioned midsole on top of a robust rubber outsole finishes the design.

This exclusive colorway was designed to celebrate the 2008 Beijing Olympics and derives from the Olympic flag aesthetics. It features an upper white leather for breathability and matching leather overlays with perforations along the bottom. The sneaker also displays black details on the lining, branding, and midsole, along with red, green, yellow, and blue accents.

The Air Jordan 6 ‘Motorsports’ dropped in 2010, featuring a design inspired by the superbike used that year by MJ’s motorsport racing team. The mid-top features a crisp white leather upper, accented with black laces and dual Jumpman and ‘23’ embroidery on the heel of each shoe. The kicks are finished with elephant print on the collar lining and a smoky black translucent outsole underfoot.

The Jordan 6 Rings is a hybrid silhouette celebrating the six championship rings of Michael Jordan by mixing components from the sneakers he wore for every championship. Originally published in 2008, in 2017 the design produced a comeback with four different colors including this classic edition of white, black and red. Signature details include Jumpman logos, branded lace locks, leather quarter straps, and an internal tongue tag graphic representing the year of each championship.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro Low BG 'Chrome' dropped in 2016, bringing back the subdued low-top colorway first seen on store shelves in 2002. The reissue is virtually identical to its predecessor, showcasing a monochromatic black nubuck upper with chrome lace locks and silver embroidered Jumpman branding. Additional metallic silver hits adorn the midsole, reinforced underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Hyper Pink' features an Anthracite and black upper with 3M reflective detailing throughout. The subtly flashy look is accented by vibrant hits of Hyper Pink on the lace lock and heel pull-tab, with more pink on the midsole speckling. Visible Air provides cushioning, with icy translucent inserts on the outsole.

Updating the retro silhouette with a distinctive color combination taken from an OG Air Jordan 7 release is the Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'Bordeaux.' The upper features black and grey nubuck with a patterned multicolor tongue directly inspired by the AJ7. Bordeaux accents can be seen on the sneaker's throat and molded spoiler-like heel tab. A tonal Jumpman icon is embroidered on the back heel, which complements the amber-colored Jumpman on the rubber outsole.

Available in kid sizes, the Air Jordan 6 Retro PS 'Bordeaux' has a palette lifted from an OG colorway of the Air Jordan 7. The upper is made from grey nubuck with perforated side panels and contrasting black nubuck overlaid throughout the midfoot, heel, and collar. Its titular hue is shown on the molded heel tab and a lace guard marked with a Jumpman logo.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro PS 'Carmine' 2021 is a preschool iteration of a shoe that brings back an OG colorway. Released in February 2021, the shoe's upper is built with a nubuck base, finished in Carmine and overlaid by white leather. Black contrast marks the open-hole tongue and heel pull-loop, while underfoot, this model forgoes the usual visible Air of its full-size counterpart.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro SE GS 'Defining Moments' 2020 is a grade-school iteration of a shoe that originally released as part of a two-pack in 2006. Faithful to the original look, the shoe's upper is built with black nubuck, accented by hits of metallic gold throughout. Underfoot, the midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole with translucent sections.
